#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; is the &kde; tool for managing <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/X.509\">&x509;</ulink> and <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Pretty_Good_Privacy#OpenPGP\">&openpgp;</ulink> certificates in the "
"<ulink url=\"https://www.gnupg.org/documentation/manuals/gnupg/Invoking-"
"GPGSM.html\">&gpgsm;</ulink> and <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"GNU_Privacy_Guard\">&gpg;</ulink> keyboxes and for retrieving certificates "
"from &ldap; and other certificate servers."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; je &kde; orodje za upravljanje <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/X.509\">&x509;</ulink> in <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Pretty_Good_Privacy#OpenPGP\">&openpgp;</ulink> potrdila v <ulink url="
"\"https://www.gnupg.org/documentation/manuals/gnupg/Invoking-GPGSM.html"
"\">&gpgsm;</ulink> in <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"GNU_Privacy_Guard\">&gpg;</ulink> predalih za ključe in za pridobivanje "
"potrdil iz &ldap; in drugih strežnikov potrdil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; can be started from &kmail;'s <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Certificate Manager</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu, "
"as well as from the command line. The &kleopatra; executable is named "
"<userinput><command>kleopatra</command></userinput>."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; lahko zaženete iz menija &kmail;a <menuchoice><guimenu>Orodja</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Upravitelj potrdil</guimenuitem></menuchoice> ali pa "
"iz ukazne vrstice. Izvršljiva datoteka kleopatre se imenuje "
"<userinput><command>kleopatra</command></userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This program is named after Cleopatra, a famous female Egyptian pharaoh that "
"lived at the time of Julius Caesar, with whom she had a child, Caesarion, "
"unacknowledged as his heir."
msgstr ""
"Ta program je poimenovan po Kleopatri, slavni egipčanski faraonji, ki je "
"živela v času Julija Cezarja, s katerim je imela otroka, Caesariona, ki ni "
"bil priznan kot njegov dedič."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The name was chosen since this program originates from the <ulink url="
"\"https://www.gnupg.org/aegypten2/\">&Auml;gypten Projects</ulink> (&Auml;"
"gypten is German for Egypt). &kleopatra; is the German spelling of Cleopatra."
msgstr ""
"Ime je bilo izbrano, ker ta program izvira iz <ulink url=\"https://www.gnupg."
"org/aegypten2/\">&Auml;gypten projektov</ulink> (&Auml;gypten je nemško za "
"Egipt). &kleopatra; je nemško črkovanje Kleopatre."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "Main Functions"
msgstr "Glavne funkcije"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid "Viewing the Local Keybox"
msgstr "Ogled lokalne ključavnice"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra;'s main function is to display and edit the contents of the local "
"keybox, which is similar to &gpg;'s concept of keyrings, albeit one should "
"not stretch this analogy too much."
msgstr ""
"Glavna funkcija programa &kleopatra; je prikazovanje in urejanje vsebine "
"lokalnega predala s tipkami, kar je podobno &gpg;-jevemu konceptu obeskov za "
"ključe, čeprav te analogije ne bi smeli preveč raztegovati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main window is divided into the large key listing area consisting of "
"several tabs, the menubar and the <link linkend=\"functions-search\">search "
"bar</link> on top, and a status bar at the bottom."
msgstr ""
"Glavno okno je razdeljeno na veliko območje s seznamom ključev, ki ga "
"sestavlja več zavihkov, menijska vrstica in <link linkend=\"functions-search"
"\">iskalna vrstica</link> na vrhu ter vrstica stanja na dnu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:153
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each line in the key list corresponds to one certificate, identified by the "
"so-called <guilabel>Subject &dn;</guilabel>. &dn; is an acronym for "
"<quote>Distinguished Name</quote>, a hierarchical identifier, much like a "
"file system path with an unusual syntax, that is supposed to globally "
"uniquely identify a given certificate."
msgstr ""
"Vsaka vrstica na seznamu ključev ustreza enemu potrdilu, označenem s tako "
"imenovano <guilabel>Zadevo &dn;</guilabel>. &dn; je akronim za "
"<quote>Distinguished Name</quote>, hierarhični identifikator, podobno kot "
"pot datotečnega sistema z nenavadno sintakso, ki naj bi globalno enolično "
"identificiral dano potrdilo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To be valid, and thus usable, (public) keys need to be signed by a &ca; "
"(Certification Authority). These signatures are called certificates, but "
"usually the terms <quote>certificate</quote> and <quote>(public) key</quote> "
"are used interchangeably, and we will not distinguish between them in this "
"manual either, except when explicitly noted."
msgstr ""
"Da bi bili (javni) ključi veljavni in torej uporabni, morajo biti podpisani "
"z &ca; (Organizacijo za potrjevanje). Ti podpisi se imenujejo potrdila, "
"vendar se običajno izraza <quote>certifikat</quote> in <quote>(javni) ključ</"
"quote> uporabljata zamenljivo in tudi v tem priročniku med njima ne bomo "
"razlikovali, razen če je to izrecno navedeno ."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&ca;s must in turn be signed by other &ca;s to be valid. Of course, this "
"must end somewhere, so the top-level &ca; (root-&ca;) signs its key with "
"itself (this is called a self-signature). Root certificates thus need to be "
"assigned validity (commonly called trust) manually, &eg; after comparing the "
"fingerprint with the one on the website of the &ca;. This is typically done "
"by the system administrator or the vendor of a product using certificates, "
"but can be done by the user via &gpgsm;'s command line interface."
msgstr ""
"&ca;-ji morajo biti podpisani s strani drugih &ca;-jev, da so veljavni. "
"Seveda se mora to nekje končati, zato najvišja raven &ca; (korenska-&ca;) "
"podpiše svoj ključ sam s seboj (to se imenuje samopodpis). Korenskim "
"potrdilom je tako treba ročno dodeliti veljavnost (običajno imenovano "
"zaupanje), npr. po primerjavi prstnega odtisa s tistim na spletni strani "
"&ca;. To običajno naredi skrbnik sistema ali prodajalec izdelka, ki "
"uporablja potrdila, vendar lahko to stori uporabnik prek vmesnika ukazne "
"vrstice &gpgsm;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To see which of the certificates are root certificates, you switch to the "
"hierarchical keylist mode with <xref linkend=\"view-hierarchical-key-list\"/"
">."
msgstr ""
"Če želite videti, katera od potrdil so korenska, preklopite v način "
"hierarhičnega seznama ključev s <xref linkend=\"view-hierarchical-key-list\"/"
">."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can see the details of any certificate by double-clicking it or using "
"<xref linkend=\"view-certificate-details\"/>. This opens a dialog that shows "
"the most common properties of the certificate, its certificate chain (&ie; "
"the chain of issuers up to the root-&ca;), and a dump of all information the "
"backend is able to extract from the certificate."
msgstr ""
"Podrobnosti katerega koli potrdila si lahko ogledate tako, da ga dvokliknete "
"ali uporabite <xref linkend=\"view-certificate-details\"/>. To odpre "
"pogovorno okno, ki prikazuje najpogostejše lastnosti potrdila, njegovo "
"verigo potrdil (tj. verigo izdajateljev do korena-&ca;) in izpis vseh "
"informacij, ki jih lahko zaledje pridobi iz potrdila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you change the keybox without using &kleopatra; (&eg; using &gpgsm;'s "
"command line interface), you can refresh the view with <xref linkend=\"view-"
"redisplay\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Če spremenite ključavnico brez uporabe programa &kleopatra; (npr. z "
"vmesnikom ukazne vrstice &gpgsm;), lahko pogled osvežite z <xref linkend="
"\"view-redisplay\"/>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:205
#, no-c-format
msgid "Searching and Importing Certificates"
msgstr "Iskanje in uvoz potrdil"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:207
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most of the time, you will acquire new certificates by verifying signatures "
"in emails, since certificates are embedded in the signatures made using them "
"most of the time. However, if you need to send a mail to someone you have "
"not yet had contact with, you need to fetch the certificate from an &ldap; "
"folder (although <ulink url=\"https://www.gnupg.org/documentation/manuals/"
"gnupg/Invoking-GPGSM.html#Invoking-GPGSM\"> &gpgsm;</ulink> can do this "
"automatically), or from a file. You also need to import your own certificate "
"after receiving the &ca; answer to your certification request."
msgstr ""
"Največkrat boste nova potrdila pridobili s preverjanjem podpisov v e-poštnih "
"sporočilih, saj so potrdila večinoma vdelana v podpise, narejene z njimi. Če "
"pa morate poslati pošto nekomu, s katerim še niste bili v stiku, morate "
"pridobiti potrdilo iz &ldap; mape (čeprav lahko <ulink url=\"https://www."
"gnupg.org/documentation/manuals/gnupg/Invoking-GPGSM.html#Invoking-GPGSM\"> "
"&gpgsm;</ulink> to stori samodejno) ali iz datoteke. Po prejemu &ca; "
"odgovora na vašo zahtevo za potrdilo morate uvoziti svoj certifikat."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To search for a certificate in an &ldap; directory, select "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Lookup Certificates on "
"Server</guimenuitem></menuchoice> and enter some text (&eg; the name of the "
"person you want the certificate for) into the line edit of the "
"<guilabel>Keyserver Certificate Lookup</guilabel> dialog, then click on the "
"<guilabel>Search</guilabel> button. The results will be displayed in the key "
"list below the search bar, where you can select certificates to look at them "
"by clicking the <guibutton>Details</guibutton> button or download them with "
"<guibutton>Import</guibutton> into the local keybox."
msgstr ""
"Za iskanje potrdila v &ldap; izberite <menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Poišči potrdila na strežniku</guimenuitem></menuchoice> "
"in v vrstico vnesite besedilo (npr. ime osebe, za katero želite potrdilo) "
"uredite pogovorno okno <guilabel>Iskanje potrdila strežnika ključev</"
"guilabel>, nato kliknite gumb <guilabel>Išči</guilabel>. Rezultati bodo "
"prikazani na seznamu ključev pod iskalno vrstico, kjer lahko izberete "
"potrdila in si jih ogledate tako, da kliknete gumb <guibutton>Podrobnosti</"
"guibutton> ali jih prenesete z <guibutton>Uvozi</guibutton> v lokalni "
"predalnik za ključe."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can configure the list of &ldap; servers to search in the <link linkend="
"\"configuration-directory-services\"><guilabel>Directory Services</"
"guilabel></link> page of &kleopatra;'s configure dialog."
msgstr ""
"Konfigurirate lahko seznam &ldap; strežnikov za iskanje na strani <link "
"linkend=\"configuration-directory-services\"><guilabel>Imeniške storitve</"
"guilabel></link> v pogovornem oknu za konfiguracijo programa &kleopatra;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you received the certificate as a file, try <xref linkend=\"file-import-"
"certificates\"/>. &gpgsm; needs to understand the format of the certificate "
"file; please refer to &gpgsm;'s manual for a list of supported file formats."
msgstr ""
"Če ste potrdilo prejeli kot datoteko, poskusite <xref linkend=\"file-import-"
"certificates\"/>. &gpgsm; mora razumeti format datoteke potrdila; seznam "
"podprtih formatov datotek najdete v priročniku &gpgsm;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you did not <link linkend=\"functions-newkey\">create your keypair with "
"&gpgsm;</link>, you also need to manually import the public key (as well as "
"the secret key) from the PKCS#12 file you got from the &ca;. You can do this "
"on the command line with <link linkend=\"commandline-option-import-"
"certificate\"><userinput><command>kleopatra <option>--import-certificate</"
"option> <filename>filename</filename></command></userinput></link> or from "
"within &kleopatra; with <xref linkend=\"file-import-certificates\"/>, just "
"as you would to for <quote>normal</quote> certificates."
msgstr ""
"Če niste <link linkend=\"functions-newkey\">ustvarili svojega para ključev z "
"&gpgsm;</link>, morate tudi ročno uvoziti javni ključ (in skrivni ključ) iz "
"datoteke PKCS#12, ki ste jo dobili iz &ca;. To lahko storite v ukazni "
"vrstici z <link linkend=\"commandline-option-import-certificate"
"\"><userinput><command>kleopatra <option>--import-certificate</option> "
"<filename>filename</filename> </command></userinput></link> ali znotraj "
"&kleopatra; z <xref linkend=\"file-import-certificates\"/>, tako kot bi to "
"storili za <quote>običajna</quote> potrdila."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:258
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating New Key Pairs"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje novih parov ključev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The menu item <xref linkend=\"file-new-key-pair\"/> starts the <guilabel>Key "
"Pair Creation Wizard</guilabel> which will guide you through a number of "
"steps to create a certificate request."
msgstr ""
"Postavka menija <xref linkend=\"file-new-key-pair\"/> zažene "
"<guilabel>Čarovnika za ustvarjanje para ključev</guilabel>, ki vas bo vodil "
"skozi številne korake za ustvarjanje zahteve za potrdilo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whenever you are done with a step in the wizard, press <guibutton>Next</"
"guibutton> to go to the next step (or <guibutton>Back</guibutton> to review "
"steps that are already completed). The certificate request creation can be "
"canceled at any time by pressing the <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Kadarkoli končate s korakom v čarovniku, pritisnite <guibutton>Naprej</"
"guibutton>, da se premaknete na naslednji korak (ali <guibutton>Nazaj</"
"guibutton>, da pregledate korake, ki so že dokončani). Ustvarjanje zahteve "
"za potrdilo lahko kadar koli prekličete s pritiskom na gumb "
"<guibutton>Prekliči</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the first page of the wizard choose which type of certificate you want to "
"create:"
msgstr ""
"Na prvi strani čarovnika izberite vrsto potrdila, ki ga želite ustvariti:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a personal OpenPGP key pair"
msgstr "Ustvarite osebni par ključev OpenPGP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&openpgp; key pairs are created locally, and certified by your friends and "
"acquaintances. There is no central certification authority; instead, every "
"individual creates a personal Web Of Trust by certifying other user's key "
"pairs with his own certificate."
msgstr ""
"&openpgp; pari ključev so ustvarjeni lokalno in potrjeni s strani vaših "
"prijateljev in znancev. Ni centralnega overitelja potrdil; namesto tega vsak "
"posameznik ustvari osebni Web Of Trust (mrežo zaupanja) s certificiranjem "
"parov ključev drugega uporabnika s svojim certifikatom."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:279
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You have to enter a <guilabel>Name</guilabel>, <guilabel>EMail</guilabel> "
"and optional a <guilabel>Comment</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Vnesti morate <guilabel>Ime</guilabel>, <guilabel>E-pošto</guilabel> in "
"neobvezno <guilabel>Komentar</guilabel>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:284
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a personal X.509 key pair and certification request"
msgstr "Ustvarite osebni par ključev X.509 in zahtevo za potrdilo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:286
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&x509; key pairs are created locally, but certified centrally by a "
"certification authority (&ca;). &ca;s can certify other &ca;s, creating a "
"central, hierarchical chain of trust."
msgstr ""
"&x509; pari ključev so ustvarjeni lokalno, vendar centralno certificirani s "
"strani certifikacijskega organa (&ca;). &ca;ji lahko certificirajo druge &ca;"
"je, s čimer ustvarijo osrednjo, hierarhično verigo zaupanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The next step in the wizard is to type in your personal data for the "
"certificate. The fields to fill out are:"
msgstr ""
"Naslednji korak v čarovniku je vnos osebnih podatkov za potrdilo. Polja za "
"izpolnitev so:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:293
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Common Name (CN):</guilabel> Your name;"
msgstr "<guilabel>Splošno ime (CN):</guilabel> Vaše ime;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Email address (EMAIL):</guilabel> Your email address; be sure to "
"type this in correctly&mdash;this will be the address people will be sending "
"mail to when they use your certificate."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>E-poštni naslov (EMAIL):</guilabel> Vaš e-poštni naslov; "
"poskrbite, da boste to pravilno vnesli &mdash; to bo naslov, na katerega "
"bodo ljudje pošiljali pošto, ko bodo uporabljali vaše potrdilo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Location (L):</guilabel> The town or city in which you live;"
msgstr "<guilabel>Lokacija (L):</guilabel> Mesto, v katerem živite;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Organizational unit (OU):</guilabel> The organizational unit you "
"are in (for example, \"Logistics\");"
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Organizacijska enota (OU):</guilabel> Organizacijska enota, v "
"kateri ste (na primer \"Logistika\");"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:308
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Organization (O):</guilabel> The organization you represent (for "
"example, the company you work for);"
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Organizacija (O):</guilabel> Organizacija, ki jo predstavljate (na "
"primer podjetje, za katerega delate);"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Country code (C):</guilabel> The two letter code for the country "
"in which you are living (for example, \"US\");"
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Koda države (C):</guilabel> Dvočrkovna koda države, v kateri "
"živite (na primer \"SI\");"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:316
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The next step in the wizard is to select whether to store the certificate in "
"a file or send it directly to a &ca;. You will have to specify the filename "
"or email address to send the certificate request to."
msgstr ""
"Naslednji korak v čarovniku je izbira, ali želite potrdilo shraniti v "
"datoteko ali ga poslati neposredno v &ca;. Določiti boste morali ime "
"datoteke ali e-poštni naslov, na katerega želite poslati zahtevo za potrdilo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid "Revoking a key"
msgstr "Preklic ključa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:329
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A key pair that has expired can be brought back into an operational state as "
"long as you have access to the private key and the passphrase. To reliably "
"render a key unusable you need to revoke it. Revoking is done by adding a "
"special revocation signature to the key."
msgstr ""
"Par ključev, ki je potekel, je mogoče vrniti v operativno stanje, če imate "
"dostop do zasebnega ključa in gesla. Če želite zanesljivo narediti ključ "
"neuporaben, ga morate preklicati. Preklic se izvede tako, da se ključu doda "
"poseben preklicni podpis."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This revocation signature is stored in a separate file. This file can later "
"be imported into the keyring and is then attached to the key rendering it "
"unusable. Please note that to import this signature to the key no password "
"is required. Therefore you should store this revocation signature in a safe "
"place, usually one that is different from you key pair. It is a good advise "
"to use a place that is detached from your computer, either copy it to an "
"external storage device like an USB stick or print it out."
msgstr ""
"Ta preklicni podpis je shranjen v ločeni datoteki. To datoteko je mogoče "
"pozneje uvoziti v datoteko s certifikati in jo nato priložiti ključu, zaradi "
"česar postane neuporabna. Upoštevajte, da za uvoz tega podpisa v ključ ni "
"potrebno geslo. Zato morate ta preklicni podpis shraniti na varno mesto, "
"običajno na mesto, ki se razlikuje od vašega para ključev. Priporočljivo je, "
"da uporabite mesto, ki ni ločeno od računalnika, kopirajte ga na zunanjo "
"napravo za shranjevanje, kot je ključek USB, ali ga natisnite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; does not provide a function to create such a revocation "
"signature at any time, but you can do that with the &kde; application &kgpg; "
"by choosing <menuchoice><guimenu>Keys</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Revoke key</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> and optionally importing the revocation signature "
"to your keyring immediately."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; ne nudi funkcije za ustvarjanje takega preklicanega podpisa "
"kadar koli, vendar lahko to storite z &kde; aplikacijo &kgpg; tako, da "
"izberete <menuchoice><guimenu>Ključi</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Prekliči ključ</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> in po želji takoj uvozite podpis za preklic v vaš "
"obesek ključev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:347
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An alternative way of generating a revocation certificate is to use &gpg; "
"directly from the command line: <userinput>gpg --output "
"<replaceable>revocation_certificate</replaceable>.asc --gen-revoke "
"<replaceable>your_key</replaceable></userinput>. The argument "
"<replaceable>your_key</replaceable> must be a key specifier, either the key "
"ID of your primary keypair or any part of a user ID that identifies your "
"keypair."
msgstr ""
"Alternativni način generiranja potrdila o preklicu je uporaba &gpg; "
"neposredno iz ukazne vrstice: <userinput>gpg --output "
"<replaceable>preklicni_certifikat</replaceable>.asc --gen-revoke "
"<replaceable>vaš_ključ</replaceable></userinput>. Argument "
"<replaceable>vaš_ključ</replaceable> mora biti specifikator ključa, bodisi "
"ID ključa vašega primarnega para ključev ali kateri koli del ID-ja "
"uporabnika, ki identificira vaš par ključev."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:375
#, no-c-format
msgid "Menu Reference"
msgstr "Referenca menija"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:377
#, no-c-format
msgid "File Menu"
msgstr "Meni Datotek"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:382
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>New Certificate...</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Novo potrdilo...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Creates a new key pair (public and private)</action> and allows to "
"send the public part to a certification authority (&ca;) for signing. The "
"resulting certificate is then sent back to you, or stored in an &ldap; "
"server for you to download into your local keybox, where you can use it to "
"sign and decrypt mails."
msgstr ""
"<action>Ustvari nov par ključev (javni in zasebni)</action> in omogoči "
"pošiljanje javnega dela overitelju (&ca;) v podpis. Dobljeno potrdilo se vam "
"nato pošlje nazaj ali shrani v &ldap; strežnik, ki ga lahko prenesete v svoj "
"lokalni predal s ključi, kjer ga lahko uporabite za podpisovanje in "
"dešifriranje pošte."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:393
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This mode of operation is called <quote>decentralized key generation</"
"quote>, since all keys are created locally. &kleopatra; (and &gpgsm;) do not "
"support <quote>centralized key generation</quote> directly, but you can "
"import the public/secret key bundle that you receive from the &ca; in "
"PKCS#12 format via <xref linkend=\"file-import-certificates\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Ta način delovanja se imenuje <quote>decentralizirano ustvarjanje ključev</"
"quote>, saj so vsi ključi ustvarjeni lokalno. &kleopatra; (in &gpgsm;) ne "
"podpirajo <quote>centraliziranega generiranja ključev</quote> neposredno, "
"lahko pa uvozite skupek javnih/skrivnih ključev, ki ga prejmete iz &ca; v "
"formatu PKCS#12 prek <xref linkend=\"file-import-certificates\"/>."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:403
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>I</keycap></"
"keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Lookup Certificates "
"on Server...</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>I</keycap></"
"keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Iskanje potrdil "
"v strežniku...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:409
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Searches for, and imports, certificates from certificate servers "
"into the local keybox.</action> See <xref linkend=\"functions-search\"/> for "
"details."
msgstr ""
"<action>Išče in uvaža potrdila s strežnikov potrdil v lokalni predal s "
"ključi.</action> Za podrobnosti glejte <xref linkend=\"functions-search\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:414
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You need to have key servers configured for this to work. See <xref linkend="
"\"configuration-directory-services\"/> for more details."
msgstr ""
"Da bo to delovalo, morate imeti konfigurirane ključne strežnike. Za več "
"podrobnosti glejte <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-services\"/>."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:425
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>I</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Import Certificates...</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>I</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Uvozi potrdila...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:431
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Imports certificates and/or secret keys from files into the local "
"keybox.</action> See <xref linkend=\"functions-search\"/> for details."
msgstr ""
"<action>Uvozi potrdila in/ali tajne ključe iz datotek v lokalni predal s "
"ključi.</action> Za podrobnosti glejte <xref linkend=\"functions-search\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:436
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The format of the certificate file must be supported by &gpgsm;/&gpg;. "
"Please refer to the &gpgsm; and &gpg; manuals for a list of supported "
"formats."
msgstr ""
"Format datoteke potrdila mora podpirati &gpgsm;/&gpg;. Glejte &gpgsm; in "
"&gpg; priročnike za seznam podprtih formatov."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>E</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Export Certificates...</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>E</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Izvozi potrdila...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exports the selected certificates to a file."
msgstr "Izvozi izbrana potrdila v datoteko."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:456
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The filename extension you choose for the export file name determines the "
"format of the export file:"
msgstr ""
"Pripona imena datoteke, ki jo izberete za ime izvozne datoteke, določa "
"obliko izvozne datoteke:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:462
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For &openpgp; certificates, <filename class=\"extension\">gpg</filename> and "
"<filename class=\"extension\">pgp</filename> will result in a binary file, "
"whereas <filename class=\"extension\">asc</filename> will result in an "
"&ascii;-armored file."
msgstr ""
"Za &openpgp; potrdila bosta, <filename class=\"extension\">gpg</filename> in "
"<filename class=\"extension\">pgp</filename> povzročila binarno datoteko, "
"medtem ko bo <filename class=\"extension\">asc</filename> povzročil &ascii;-"
"oklepno datoteko."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:472
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For &smime; certificates, <filename class=\"extension\">der</filename> will "
"result in a binary, &der;-encoded file, whereas <filename class=\"extension"
"\">pem</filename> will result in an &ascii;-armored file."
msgstr ""
"Za &smime; potrdila, bo <filename class=\"extension\">der</filename> "
"povzročilo binarno, &der;-kodirano datoteko, medtem ko bo <filename class="
"\"extension\">pem</filename> povzročilo &ascii;-oklepno datoteko."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:481
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unless multiple certificates are selected, &kleopatra; will propose "
"<filename><replaceable>fingerprint</replaceable>.{asc,pem}</filename> as the "
"export file name."
msgstr ""
"Razen če je izbranih več potrdil bo, &kleopatra; kot ime izvozne datoteke "
"predlagala <filename><replaceable>prstni odtis</replaceable>.{asc,pem}</"
"filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available when one or more certificates have been "
"selected."
msgstr "Ta funkcija je na voljo samo, če je izbrano eno ali več potrdil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:492
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function exports only the public keys, even if the secret key is "
"available. Use <xref linkend=\"file-export-secret-key\"/> to export the "
"secret keys into a file."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija izvozi samo javne ključe, tudi če je skrivni ključ na voljo. Za "
"izvoz skrivnih ključev v datoteko uporabite <xref linkend=\"file-export-"
"secret-key\"/>."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:504
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Export Secret Keys...</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Izvoz skrivnih ključev...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:510
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exports the secret key to a file."
msgstr "Izvozi tajni ključ v datoteko."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:512
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the dialog that opens, you can choose whether to create a binary or an "
"&ascii;-armored export file (<guilabel>ASCII armor</guilabel>). Next click "
"on the folder icon at the right hand side of the <guilabel>Output file</"
"guilabel> text box and select folder and name of the export file. When "
"exporting &smime; secret keys, you can also choose the <guilabel>Passphrase "
"charset</guilabel>. See the discussion of the <option>--p12-charset&nbsp;"
"<replaceable>charset</replaceable></option> option in the &gpgsm; manual for "
"more details."
msgstr ""
"V pogovornem oknu, ki se odpre, lahko izberete, ali želite ustvariti binarno "
"ali &ascii;-oklepno izvozno datoteko (<guilabel>ASCII oklep</guilabel>). "
"Nato kliknite ikono mape na desni strani besedilnega polja <guilabel>Izhodna "
"datoteka</guilabel> ter izberite mapo in ime izvozne datoteke. Pri izvozu "
"&smime; skrivnih ključev, lahko izberete tudi <guilabel>Nabor znakov gesla</"
"guilabel>. Oglejte si razpravo o možnosti <option>--p12-charset&nbsp;"
"<replaceable>charset</replaceable></option> v &gpgsm; priročniku za več "
"podrobnosti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:525
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available when exactly one certificate has been "
"selected, and the secret key for that certificate is available."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo le, če je izbran natanko en certifikat in je na "
"voljo skrivni ključ tega certifikata."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:531
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It should rarely be necessary to use this function, and if it is, it should "
"be carefully planned. Planning the migration of a secret key involves choice "
"of transport media and secure deletion of the key data on the old machine, "
"as well as on the transport medium, among other things."
msgstr ""
"To funkcijo je treba uporabljati le redko, če pa jo je, jo je treba skrbno "
"načrtovati. Načrtovanje selitve tajnega ključa med drugim vključuje izbiro "
"transportnega medija in varno brisanje ključnih podatkov na starem stroju, "
"pa tudi na transportnem mediju."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:545
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>E</keycap></"
"keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Export Certificates "
"to Server...</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>E</keycap></"
"keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Izvozi potrdila "
"v strežnik...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:551
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Publish the selected certificates on a keyserver</action> (&openpgp; "
"only)."
msgstr ""
"<action>Objavi izbrana potrdila na strežniške ključe</action> (samo "
"&openpgp;)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:555
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The certificate is sent to the certificate server configured for &openpgp; "
"(cf.&nbsp;<xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-services\"/>), if that is "
"set, otherwise to <systemitem class=\"systemname\">keys.gnupg.net</"
"systemitem>."
msgstr ""
"Potrdilo je poslano na strežnik potrdil, konfiguriran za &openpgp; (npr."
"&nbsp;<xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-services\"/>), če je to "
"nastavljeno, sicer na <systemitem class=\"systemname\">keys.gnupg.net</"
"systemitem>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:562
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available if at least one &openpgp; (and no &smime;) "
"certificates have been selected."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo le, če je vsaj en &openpgp; (in nobeno potrdilo "
"&smime;) izbran."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:570
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When &openpgp; certificates have been exported to a public directory server, "
"it is nearly impossible to remove them again. Before exporting your "
"certificate to a public directory server, make sure that you have created a "
"revocation certificate so you can revoke the certificate if needed later."
msgstr ""
"Ko so bili &openpgp; certifikati izvoženi v javni imeniški strežnik, jih je "
"skoraj nemogoče znova odstraniti. Preden izvozite svoje potrdilo v javni "
"imeniški strežnik, se prepričajte, da ste ustvarili potrdilo o preklicu, da "
"ga lahko pozneje po potrebi prekličete."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most public &openpgp; certificate servers synchronize certificates amongst "
"each other, so there is little point in sending to more than one."
msgstr ""
"Večina javnih &openpgp; strežnikov potrdil sinhronizirajo potrdila med "
"seboj, zato nima smisla pošiljati več kot enemu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:585
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It can happen that a search on a certificate server turns up no results even "
"though you just have sent your certificate there. This is because most "
"public keyserver addresses use <acronym>DNS</acronym> round-robin to balance "
"the load over multiple machines. These machines synchronize with each other, "
"but usually only every 24 hours or so."
msgstr ""
"Lahko se zgodi, da iskanje na strežniku potrdil ne prinese nobenih "
"rezultatov, čeprav ste potrdilo pravkar poslali tja. To je zato, ker večina "
"naslovov javnih strežnikov ključev uporablja <acronym>DNS</acronym> krožno "
"za uravnoteženje obremenitve več naprav. Te naprave se med seboj "
"sinhronizirajo, vendar običajno le vsakih 24 ur."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Decrypt/Verify Files...</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Dešifriraj/preveri datoteke...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:605
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Decrypts files and/or verifies signatures</action> over files."
msgstr ""
"<action>Dešifrira datoteke in/ali preveri podpise</action> nad datotekami."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:619
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Sign/Encrypt Files...</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Podpiši/šifriraj datotek...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:625
#, no-c-format
msgid "Signs and/or encrypts files."
msgstr "Podpiše in/ali šifrira datoteke."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:640
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>W</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Close</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>W</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Zapri</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:646
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Closes &kleopatra;'s main window.</action> You can restore it from "
"the system tray icon at any time."
msgstr ""
"<action>Zapre glavno okno programa &kleopatra;</action> Kadar koli ga lahko "
"obnovite z ikono v sistemski vrstici."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:654
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Quit</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Zapri</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:658
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminates &kleopatra;."
msgstr "Konča program &kleopatra;."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:668
#, no-c-format
msgid "View Menu"
msgstr "Ogled menija"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\"><keycap>F5</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Redisplay</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\"><keycap>F5</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ponovni prikaz</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:681
#, no-c-format
msgid "Refreshes the certificate list."
msgstr "Osveži seznam potrdil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:683
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using this function is usually not necessary, as &kleopatra; monitors the "
"file system for changes and automatically refreshes the certificate list "
"when needed."
msgstr ""
"Uporaba te funkcije običajno ni potrebna, saj &kleopatra; spremlja datotečni "
"sistem glede sprememb in po potrebi samodejno osveži seznam potrdil."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:695
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Esc;</keycombo></shortcut> "
"<guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Stop Operation</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Esc;</keycombo></shortcut> "
"<guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ustavi operacijo</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:701
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Stops (cancels) all pending operations,</action> &eg; a search, "
"keylisting, or a download."
msgstr ""
"<action>Ustavi (prekliče) vse čakajoče operacije,</action> npr. iskanje, "
"seznam ključev ali prenos."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:705
#, no-c-format
msgid "This function is only available if at least one operation is active."
msgstr "Ta funkcija je na voljo le, če je aktivna vsaj ena operacija."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:710
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Due to backend limitations, sometimes operations will hang in such a way "
"that this function won't be able to cancel them, right away, or at all."
msgstr ""
"Zaradi omejitev zaledja bodo včasih operacije tako obvisele, da jih ta "
"funkcija ne bo mogla preklicati takoj ali sploh."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:715
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In such cases, the only way to restore order is to kill &scdaemon;, "
"&dirmngr;, &gpgsm; and &gpg; processes, in that order, via the operating "
"system tools (<command>top</command>, Task-Manager, &etc;), until the "
"operation get unblocked."
msgstr ""
"V takih primerih je edini način za vzpostavitev reda ta, da ustavite "
"&scdaemon;, &dirmngr;, &gpgsm; in &gpg; procese v tem vrstnem redu prek "
"orodij operacijskega sistema (<command>vrh</command>, Task-Manager itd.), "
"dokler se operacija ne odblokira."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:728
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Certificate Details</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Ogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>Podrobnosti o potrdilu</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:731
#, no-c-format
msgid "Shows the details of the currently selected certificate."
msgstr "Prikaže podrobnosti trenutno izbranega potrdila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:734
#, no-c-format
msgid "This function is only available if exactly one certificate is selected."
msgstr "Ta funkcija je na voljo samo, če je izbran natanko en certifikat."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:737
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is also available by double-clicking the corresponding item in "
"the list view directly."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo tudi tako, da neposredno dvokliknete ustrezni "
"element v pogledu seznama."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:746
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Hierarchical Certificate List</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>Hierarhični seznam potrdil</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:749
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toggles between hierarchical and flat certificate list mode."
msgstr "Preklaplja med hierarhičnim in ravnim načinom seznama potrdil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:752
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In hierarchical mode, certificates are arranged in issuer/subject relation, "
"so it is easy to see which certification hierarchy a given certificate "
"belongs to, but a given certificate is harder to find initially (though you "
"can of course use the <link linkend=\"functions-search\">search bar</link>)."
msgstr ""
"V hierarhičnem načinu so potrdila urejena v razmerju izdajatelj/subjekt, "
"tako da je enostavno videti, kateri certifikacijski hierarhiji pripada dano "
"potrdilo, vendar je dano potrdilo na začetku težje najti (čeprav lahko "
"seveda uporabite <link linkend=\"functions-search\">iskalno vrstico</link>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:758
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In flat mode, all certificates are displayed in a flat list, sorted "
"alphabetically. In this mode, a given certificate is easy to find, but it is "
"not directly clear which root certificate it belongs to."
msgstr ""
"V ploščatem načinu so vsa potrdila prikazana na ploščatem seznamu, "
"razvrščena po abecedi. V tem načinu je določeno potrdilo preprosto najti, "
"vendar ni neposredno jasno, kateremu korenskemu potrdilu pripada."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:763
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function toggles hierarchical mode per tab, &ie; each tab has its own "
"hierarchy state. This is so that you can have both a flat and a hierarchical "
"listing at hand, each in its own tab."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija preklopi hierarhični način na zavihek, tj. vsak zavihek ima "
"svoje hierarhično stanje. To je zato, da imate lahko pri roki pavšalni in "
"hierarhični seznam, vsakega v svojem zavihku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:771
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Hierarchical display is currently only implemented for &smime; certificates. "
"There is disagreement amongst the developers regarding the correct way to "
"display &openpgp; certificates hierarchically (basically, <quote>parent "
"&equals; signer</quote> or <quote>parent &equals; signee</quote>)."
msgstr ""
"Hierarhični prikaz je trenutno implementiran samo za &smime; potrdila. Med "
"razvijalci obstaja nesoglasje glede pravilnega načina prikaza &openpgp; "
"potrdila hierarhično (v bistvu, <quote>nadrejeni je podpisnik</quote> ali "
"<quote>nadrejeni je tisti, ki prejme podpisano datoteko</quote>)."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:786
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>.</keycap> </keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Expand All</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>.</keycap> </keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>Razširi vse</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:790
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Expands all list items in the certificate list view,</action> &ie; "
"makes all items visible."
msgstr ""
"<action>Razširi vse elemente seznama v pogledu seznama potrdil,</action>tj. "
"naredi vse elemente vidne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:793
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is the default when entering hierarchical keylist mode."
msgstr "To je privzeto pri vstopu v način hierarhičnega seznama tipk."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:796 index.docbook:813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can still expand and collapse each individual item by itself, of course."
msgstr "Seveda lahko še vedno razširite in strnete vsak posamezen element."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:799 index.docbook:816
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available when <xref linkend=\"view-hierarchical-key-"
"list\"/> is on."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo samo, če je vklopljen <xref linkend=\"view-"
"hierarchical-key-list\"/>."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:806
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>,</keycap> </keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu>View</guimenu><guimenuitem>Collapse All</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>,</keycap> </keycombo></"
"shortcut><guimenu>Pogled</guimenu><guimenuitem>Strni vse</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:810
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Collapses all list items in the certificate list view,</action> &ie; "
"hides all but the top-level items."
msgstr ""
"<action>Strni vse elemente seznama v pogledu seznama potrdil,</action> tj. "
"skrije vse razen elementov najvišje ravni."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:825
#, no-c-format
msgid "Certificates Menu"
msgstr "Meni potrdil"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:831
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Certificates</guimenu><guimenuitem>Change Owner Trust...</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Potrdila</guimenu><guimenuitem>Spremeni zaupanje lastnika...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:837
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changes the Owner Trust of the selected &openpgp; certificate."
msgstr "Spremeni zaupanje lastnika izbranega &openpgp; potrdila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:843
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available when exactly one &openpgp; certificate is "
"selected."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo le, če je natanko eno &openpgp; potrdilo izbrano."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:852
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Certificates</guimenu><guimenuitem>Trust Root Certificate</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Potrdila</guimenu><guimenuitem>Zaupanja vredno korensko potrdilo</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:858
#, no-c-format
msgid "Marks this (&smime;) root certificate as trusted."
msgstr "Označi to (&smime;) korensko potrdilo kot zaupanja vredno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:860
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some ways, this is the equivalent of <xref linkend=\"certificates-change-"
"owner-trust\"/> for &smime; root certificates. You can, however, only choose "
"between&mdash;in &openpgp; terms&mdash;<quote>ultimate</quote> trust and "
"<quote>never trust</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Na nek način je to enakovredno <xref linkend=\"certificates-change-owner-"
"trust\"/> za &smime; korenska potrdila. Izbirate pa lahko le med &mdash; v "
"&openpgp; izrazema &mdash;<quote>skrajno</quote> zaupanje in <quote>nikoli "
"ne zaupati</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:869
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The backend (by way of &gpgagent;) will ask at root certificate import time "
"whether to trust the imported root certificate. However, that function must "
"be explicitly enabled in the backend configuration (<option>allow-mark-"
"trusted</option> in <filename>gpg-agent.conf</filename>, or either "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>GnuPG&nbsp;System</guimenu> <guisubmenu>GPG&nbsp;Agent</"
"guisubmenu> <guimenuitem>Allow clients to mark keys as \"trusted\"</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> or <link linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation-"
"allow-mark-trusted\"><menuchoice><guimenu>S/MIME&nbsp;Validation</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Allow to mark root certificates as trusted</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice></link> under <xref linkend=\"configuration\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"Zaledje (preko &gpgagent;) bo ob času uvoza korenskega potrdila vprašalo, "
"ali naj zaupa uvoženemu korenskemu potrdilu. Vendar mora biti ta funkcija "
"izrecno omogočena v konfiguraciji zaledja (<option>allow-mark-trusted</"
"option> v <filename>gpg-agent.conf</filename> ali "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>GnuPG&nbsp;System </guimenu> <guisubmenu>GPG&nbsp;"
"Agent</guisubmenu> <guimenuitem>Omogoči strankam, da označijo ključe kot "
"\"zaupanja vredne\"</guimenuitem></menuchoice> ali <link linkend="
"\"configuration-smime-validation-allow-mark-trusted\"><menuchoice><guimenu>S/"
"MIME&nbsp;Validation</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Omogoči označevanje korenskih "
"potrdil kot zaupanja vrednih</guimenuitem></menuchoice></link> pod <xref "
"linkend=\"configuration\"/> )."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:885
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enabling that functionality in the backend can lead to popups from "
"&pinentry; at inopportune times (&eg; when verifying signatures), and can "
"thus block unattended email processing. For that reason, and because it is "
"desirable to be able to <emphasis>distrust</emphasis> a trusted root "
"certificate again, &kleopatra; allows manual setting of trust."
msgstr ""
"Omogočanje te funkcije v ozadju lahko povzroči pojavna okna &pinentry; ob "
"neprimernem času (npr. pri preverjanju podpisov) in lahko tako blokira "
"nenadzorovano obdelavo e-pošte. Iz tega razloga in ker je zaželeno, da lahko "
"ponovno <emphasis>ne zaupamo</emphasis> zaupanja vrednemu korenskemu "
"potrdilu, &kleopatra; omogoča ročno nastavitev zaupanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:896
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Due to lack of backend support for this function, &kleopatra; needs to work "
"directly on the &gpgsm; trust database (<filename>trustlist.txt</filename>). "
"When using this function, make sure no other crypto operations are in "
"progress that could race with &kleopatra; for modifications to that database."
msgstr ""
"Zaradi pomanjkanja zaledne podpore za to funkcijo mora &kleopatra; delovati "
"neposredno na &gpgsm; zbirki podatkov zaupanja (<filename>trustlist.txt</"
"filename>). Ko uporabljate to funkcijo, se prepričajte, da ne potekajo druge "
"kripto operacije, ki bi lahko tekmovale z programom &kleopatra; za spremembe "
"te baze podatkov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:906
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available when exactly one &smime; root certificate is "
"selected, and that certificate is not yet trusted."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo le, če je izbrano natanko eno &smime; korensko "
"potrdilo in to potrdilo še ni zaupanja vredno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:911
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use <xref linkend=\"certificates-distrust-root\"/> to undo this function."
msgstr ""
"Za razveljavitev te funkcije uporabite <xref linkend=\"certificates-distrust-"
"root\"/>."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:920
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Certificates</guimenu><guimenuitem>Distrust Root Certificate</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Potrdila</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ne zaupaj korenskemu potrdilu</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:926
#, no-c-format
msgid "Marks this (&smime;) root certificate as not trusted."
msgstr "Označi to (&smime;) korensko potrdilo kot nezaupljivo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:928
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available when exactly one &smime; root certificate is "
"selected, and that certificate is currently trusted."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo le, če je izbrano natanko eno &smime; korensko "
"potrdilo in je to potrdilo trenutno zaupanja vredno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:933
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Used to undo <xref linkend=\"certificates-trust-root\"/>. See there for "
"details."
msgstr ""
"Uporablja se za razveljavitev <xref linkend=\"certificates-trust-root\"/>. "
"Glejte tam za podrobnosti."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:943
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Certificates</guimenu><guimenuitem>Certify Certificate...</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Potrdila</guimenu><guimenuitem>Potrdi potrdilo...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:949
#, no-c-format
msgid "Allows you to certify another &openpgp; certificate."
msgstr "Omogoča vam, da potrdite drugo &openpgp; potrdilo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:955
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available if exactly one &openpgp; certificate is "
"selected."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo le, če je izbrano natanko eno &openpgp; potrdilo."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1014
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Certificates</guimenu><guimenuitem>Change Expiry Date...</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Potrdila</guimenu><guimenuitem>Spremeni datum poteka...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:1020
#, no-c-format
msgid "Allows to change the expiry date of your &openpgp; certificate."
msgstr "Omogoča spreminjanje datuma poteka vašega &openpgp; potrdila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1022
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use this function to extend the lifetime of your &openpgp; certificates as "
"an alternative to either creating a new one, or using unlimited lifetime "
"(<quote>never expires</quote>)."
msgstr ""
"S to funkcijo podaljšajte življenjsko dobo vašega &openpgp; potrdila kot "
"alternativo ustvarjanju novega ali uporabi neomejene življenjske dobe "
"(<quote>nikoli ne poteče</quote>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1028
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available if exactly one &openpgp; certificate is "
"selected, and the secret key is available for that certificate."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo le, če je izbrano natanko eno &openpgp; potrdilo in "
"je skrivni ključ na voljo za to potrdilo."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1038
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Certificates</guimenu><guimenuitem>Change Passphrase...</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Potrdila</guimenu><guimenuitem>Spremeni geslo...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:1044
#, no-c-format
msgid "Allows to change the passphrase of your secret key."
msgstr "Omogoča spreminjanje gesla vašega tajnega ključa."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1046
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available if exactly one certificate is selected, and "
"the secret key is available for that certificate. It requires a very recent "
"backend, since we changed the implementation from direct calling of &gpg; "
"and &gpgsm; to a &gpgme;-based one."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo le, če je izbrano točno eno potrdilo in je za to "
"potrdilo na voljo tajni ključ. Zahteva zelo nedavno zaledje, saj smo "
"implementacijo spremenili z neposrednega klicanja &gpg; in &gpgsm; na "
"&gpgme;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1054
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For security reasons, both the old as well as the new passphrase is asked "
"for by &pinentry;, a separate process. Depending on the platform you are "
"running on and on the quality of the &pinentry; implementation on that "
"platform, it may happen that the &pinentry; window comes up in the "
"background. So, if you select this function and nothing happens, check the "
"operating system's task bar in case a &pinentry; window is open in the "
"background."
msgstr ""
"Iz varnostnih razlogov zahteva &pinentry; tako staro kot novo geslo, ločen "
"postopek. Odvisno od platforme, na kateri delujete, in od kakovosti "
"&pinentry; implementacije na tej platformi, se lahko zgodi, da se v ozadju "
"pojavi &pinentry; okno. Torej, če izberete to funkcijo in se nič ne zgodi, "
"preverite opravilno vrstico operacijskega sistema, če je &pinentry; okno "
"odprto v ozadju."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1071
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Certificates</guimenu><guimenuitem>Add User-ID...</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Potrdila</guimenu><guimenuitem>Dodaj ID uporabnika...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:1077
#, no-c-format
msgid "Allows to add a new User-ID to your &openpgp; certificate."
msgstr ""
"Omogoča dodajanje novega uporabniškega ID-ja vašemu &openpgp; potrdilu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1079
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use this to add new identities to an existing certificate as an alternative "
"to creating a new key pair. An &openpgp; user-ID has the following form:"
msgstr ""
"Uporabite to za dodajanje novih identitet obstoječemu potrdilu kot "
"alternativo ustvarjanju novega para ključev. &openpgp; ID uporabnika ima "
"naslednjo obliko:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1084
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<replaceable>Real&nbsp;Name</replaceable>&nbsp;"
"<optional>(<replaceable>Comment</replaceable>)</optional>&nbsp;&lt;"
"<replaceable>Email</replaceable>&gt;"
msgstr ""
"<replaceable>Pravo&nbsp;Ime</replaceable>&nbsp;"
"<optional>(<replaceable>Komentar</replaceable>)</optional>&nbsp;&lt;"
"<replaceable>E-pošta</replaceable>&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1085
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the dialog that comes up when you select this function, &kleopatra; will "
"ask you for each of the three parameters (<replaceable>Real&nbsp;Name</"
"replaceable>, <replaceable>Comment</replaceable> and <replaceable>Email</"
"replaceable>) separately, and display the result in a preview."
msgstr ""
"V pogovornem oknu, ki se prikaže, ko izberete to funkcijo, vas bo program "
"&kleopatra; vprašal za vsakega od treh parametrov (<replaceable>Pravo&nbsp;"
"Ime</replaceable>, <replaceable>Komentar</replaceable> in <replaceable>E-"
"pošto</replaceable>) posebej in prikazal rezultat v predogledu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1094
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These parameters are subject to the same Administrator restrictions as in "
"new certificates. See <xref linkend=\"functions-newkey\"/> and <xref linkend="
"\"admin-certificate-request-wizard\"/> for details."
msgstr ""
"Za te parametre veljajo enake skrbniške omejitve kot za nova potrdila. Za "
"podrobnosti glejte <xref linkend=\"functions-newkey\"/> in <xref linkend="
"\"admin-certificate-request-wizard\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is only available when exactly one &openpgp; certificate is "
"selected, and the secret key is available for that certificate."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija je na voljo le, če je natanko eno &openpgp; potrdilo izbrano in "
"je skrivni ključ na voljo za to potrdilo."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\"><keycap>Del</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Certificates</guimenu><guimenuitem>Delete</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\"><keycap>Del</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Potrdila</guimenu><guimenuitem>Izbriši</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Deletes the selected certificates</action> from the local keyring."
msgstr "<action>Izbriše izbrana potrdila</action> iz lokalnega obeska ključev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use this function to remove unused keys from your local keybox. However, "
"since certificates are typically attached to signed emails, verifying an "
"email might result in the key just removed to pop back into the local "
"keybox. So it is probably best to avoid using this function as much as "
"possible. When you are lost, use the <link linkend=\"functions-search"
"\">search bar</link> or the <xref linkend=\"view-hierarchical-key-list\"/> "
"function to regain control over the lot of certificates."
msgstr ""
"S to funkcijo odstranite neuporabljene ključe iz lokalnega predala s ključi. "
"Ker pa so potrdila običajno priložena podpisanim e-poštnim sporočilom, lahko "
"preverjanje e-poštnega sporočila povzroči, da se ključ, ki je bil pravkar "
"odstranjen, vrne v lokalni nabiralnik s ključi. Zato je verjetno najbolje, "
"da se tej funkciji čim bolj izogibate. Ko se izgubite, uporabite <link "
"linkend=\"functions-search\">iskalno vrstico</link> ali funkcijo <xref "
"linkend=\"view-hierarchical-key-list\"/>, da ponovno pridobite nadzor nad "
"množico potrdil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is one exception to the above: When you delete one of your own "
"certificates, you delete the secret key along with it. This implies that you "
"will not be able to read past communication encrypted to you using this "
"certificate, unless you have a backup somewhere."
msgstr ""
"Od zgoraj navedenega obstaja ena izjema: Ko izbrišete enega od svojih "
"potrdil, izbrišete skrivni ključ skupaj z njim. To pomeni, da ne boste mogli "
"brati pretekle komunikacije, šifrirane do vas s tem potrdilom, razen če "
"imate nekje varnostno kopijo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1142
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kleopatra; will warn you when you attempt to delete a secret key."
msgstr ""
"program &kleopatra; vas bo opozoril, ko boste poskušali izbrisati skrivni "
"ključ."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Due to the hierarchical nature of &smime; certificates, if you delete an "
"&smime; issuer certificate (&ca; certificate), all subjects are deleted, too."
msgstr ""
"Zaradi hierarhične narave &smime; potrdila, če izbrišete &smime; potrdilo "
"izdajatelja (&ca; potrdilo), bodo izbrisani tudi vsi subjekti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1150
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the same as a filesystem: When you delete a folder, you delete all "
"files and folders in it, too."
msgstr ""
"To je enako kot datotečni sistem: ko izbrišete mapo, izbrišete tudi vse "
"datoteke in mape v njej."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1154
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Naturally, this function is only available if you selected at least one "
"certificate."
msgstr "Ta funkcija je seveda na voljo le, če ste izbrali vsaj en certifikat."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1163
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Certificates</guimenu><guimenuitem>Dump Certificate</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Potrdila</guimenu><guimenuitem>Izpis potrdila</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:1169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows all information that &gpgsm; has about the selected (&smime;) "
"certificate."
msgstr ""
"Prikaže vse informacije, ki jih ima &gpgsm; o izbranem (&smime;) potrdilu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See the discussion about <option>--dump-key&nbsp;<replaceable>key</"
"replaceable></option> in the &gpgsm; manual for details about the output."
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si razpravo o <option>--dump-key&nbsp;<replaceable>ključu</"
"replaceable></option> v &gpgsm; priročniku za podrobnosti o izhodu."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1193
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tools Menu"
msgstr "Meni Orodij"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1199
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>GnuPG Log Viewer...</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Orodja</guimenu><guimenuitem>Pregledovalnik dnevnikov GnuPG...</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Starts <ulink url=\"help:/kwatchgnupg/index.html\">&kwatchgnupg;</"
"ulink></action>, a tool to present the debug output of &gnupg; applications. "
"If signing, encryption, or verification mysteriously stop working, you might "
"find out why by looking at the log."
msgstr ""
"<action>Zažene <ulink url=\"help:/kwatchgnupg/index.html\">&kwatchgnupg;</"
"ulink></action>, orodje za predstavitev rezultatov odpravljanja napak "
"&gnupg; aplikacije. Če podpisovanje, šifriranje ali preverjanje skrivnostno "
"prenehajo delovati, lahko ugotovite, zakaj, če pogledate dnevnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1212
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This function is not available on &Windows;, since the underlying mechanisms "
"are not implemented in the backend on that platform."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija ni na voljo v &Windows;ih, ker osnovni mehanizmi niso "
"implementirani v ozadju te platforme."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1222
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Refresh OpenPGP Certificates</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Orodja</guimenu><guimenuitem>Osveži potrdila OpenPGP</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1227
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Refreshes all &openpgp; certificates</action> by executing "
"<programlisting><command>gpg&nbsp;<option>--refresh-keys</option></command></"
"programlisting> After successful completion of the command, your local "
"keystore will reflect the latest changes with respect to validity of "
"&openpgp; certificates."
msgstr ""
"<action>Osveži vsa &openpgp; potrdila</action> z izvedbo "
"<programlisting><command>gpg&nbsp;<option>--refresh-keys</option></command></"
"programlisting> Po uspešnem zaključku ukaza bo vaša lokalna shramba ključev "
"odražala najnovejše spremembe v zvezi z veljavnostjo &openpgp; potrdila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See note under <xref linkend=\"certificates-refresh-x509\"/> for some "
"caveats."
msgstr ""
"Glejte opombo pod <xref linkend=\"certificates-refresh-x509\"/> za nekaj "
"opozoril."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Refresh X.509 Certificates</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Orodja</guimenu><guimenuitem>Osveži potrdila X.509</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1250
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Refreshes all &smime; certificates</action> by executing "
"<programlisting><!--\n"
"                --><command>gpgsm&nbsp;<!--\n"
"                  --><option>-k</option>&nbsp;<!--\n"
"                  --><option>--with-validation</option>&nbsp;<!--\n"
"                  --><option>--force-crl-refresh</option>&nbsp;<!--\n"
"                  --><option>--enable-crl-checks</option><!--\n"
"                  --></command></programlisting> After successful completion "
"of the command, your local keystore will reflect the latest changes with "
"respect to validity of &smime; certificates."
msgstr ""
"<action>Osveži vsa &smime; potrdila</action> z izvajanjem "
"<programlisting><!--\n"
"                --><command>gpgsm&nbsp;<!--\n"
"                  --><option>-k</option>&nbsp;<!--\n"
"                  --><option>--with-validation</option>&nbsp;<!--\n"
"                  --><option>--force-crl-refresh</option>&nbsp;<!--\n"
"                  --><option>--enable-crl-checks</option><!--\n"
"                  --></command></programlisting> Po uspešnem zaključku ukaza "
"bo vaša lokalna shramba ključev odražala zadnje spremembe v zvezi z "
"veljavnostjo &smime; potrdila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Refreshing &x509; or &openpgp; certificates implies downloading all "
"certificates and &crl;s, to check if any of them have been revoked in the "
"meantime."
msgstr ""
"Osvežitev &x509; ali &openpgp; potrdil pomeni prenos vseh potrdil in &crl;"
"jev da preverite, ali je bilo katero od njih medtem preklicano."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1265
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This can put a severe strain on your own as well as other people's network "
"connections, and can take up to an hour or more to complete, depending on "
"your network connection, and the number of certificates to check."
msgstr ""
"To lahko močno obremeni vaše lastne omrežne povezave in omrežne povezave "
"drugih oseb ter lahko traja do eno uro ali več, odvisno od vaše omrežne "
"povezave in števila potrdil, ki jih je treba preveriti."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1277
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Import CRL From File...</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Orodja</guimenu><guimenuitem>Uvozi CRL iz datoteke...</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:1283
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lets you manually import &crl;s from files."
msgstr "Omogoča vam ročni uvoz &crl; iz datotek."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1286
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Normally, Certificate Revocation Lists (&crl;s) are handled transparently by "
"the backend, but it can sometimes be useful to import a &crl; manually into "
"the local &crl; cache."
msgstr ""
"Običajno zaledje pregledno obravnava sezname preklicanih potrdil (&crl;ov), "
"vendar je včasih lahko koristno &crl; uvoziti ročno v lokalni &crl; "
"predpomnilnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For &crl; import to work, the &dirmngr; tool must be in the search "
"<envar>PATH</envar>. If this menu item is disabled, you should contact the "
"system administrator and ask them to install &dirmngr;."
msgstr ""
"Za pravilno delovanje &crl; uvoza, mora biti &dirmngr; orodje v iskalnem "
"<envar>PATH</envar>u. Če je ta element menija onemogočen, se morate obrniti "
"na skrbnika sistema in ga prositi, da namesti &dirmngr;."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1308
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Clear CRL Cache</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Orodja</guimenu><guimenuitem>Počisti predpomnilnik CRL</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:1311
#, no-c-format
msgid "Clears the &gpgsm; &crl; cache."
msgstr "Počisti &gpgsm; &crl; predpomnilnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You probably never need this. You can force a refresh of the &crl; cache by "
"selecting all certificates and using <xref linkend=\"certificates-refresh-"
"x509\"/> instead."
msgstr ""
"Tega verjetno nikoli ne boste potrebovali. Lahko vsilite osvežitev &crl; "
"predpomnilnika tako, da izberete vsa potrdila in namesto tega uporabite "
"<xref linkend=\"certificates-refresh-x509\"/>."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1319
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Dump CRL Cache</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Orodja</guimenu><guimenuitem>Izpis predpomnilnika CRL</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:1322
#, no-c-format
msgid "Shows the detailed contents of the &gpgsm; &crl; cache."
msgstr "Prikaže podrobno vsebino datoteke &gpgsm; &crl; predpomnilnik."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1345
#, no-c-format
msgid "Settings Menu"
msgstr "Meni z nastavitvami"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1347
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; has a default &kde; <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> menu as "
"described in the <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-settings"
"\">&kde; Fundamentals</ulink> with one additional entry:"
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; ima privzeti &kde; Meni <guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu>, kot je "
"opisano v <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-settings\">&kde; "
"Osnove</ulink> z enim dodatnim vnosom:"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:1355
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Perform Self-Test</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu><guimenuitem>Izvedi samotestiranje</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:1361
#, no-c-format
msgid "Performs a set of self-tests and presents their result."
msgstr "Izvede niz samotestiranja in predstavi njihov rezultat."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the same set of tests that is run at startup by default. If you "
"disabled startup-time self-tests, you can re-enable them here."
msgstr ""
"To je isti niz testov, ki se privzeto izvaja ob zagonu. Če ste onemogočili "
"samopreizkuse ob zagonu, jih lahko znova omogočite tukaj."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1380
#, no-c-format
msgid "Window Menu"
msgstr "Okenski meni"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1381
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guimenu>Window</guimenu> menu allows you to manage the tabs. Using the "
"items in this menu you can rename a tab, add a new tab, duplicate the "
"current tab, close the current tab, and move the current tab to the left or "
"right."
msgstr ""
"Meni <guimenu>Okno</guimenu> omogoča upravljanje zavihkov. Z uporabo "
"elementov v tem meniju lahko preimenujete zavihek, dodate nov zavihek, "
"podvojite trenutni zavihek, zaprete trenutni zavihek in premaknete trenutni "
"zavihek v levo ali desno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By clicking with the &RMB; click on a tab you open a context menu, where you "
"can also select the same actions."
msgstr ""
"S klikom z desnim klikom miške na zavihek se odpre kontekstni meni, kjer "
"lahko tudi izberete ista dejanja."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1387
#, no-c-format
msgid "Help Menu"
msgstr "Meni pomoči"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1389
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; has a default &kde; <guimenu>Help</guimenu> menu as described in "
"the <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-help\">&kde; "
"Fundamentals</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; ima privzeti &kde; Meni <guimenu>Pomoč</guimenu>, kot je opisano "
"v <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-help\">&kde; Osnove</"
"ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1396
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Line Options Reference"
msgstr "Referenca možnosti ukazne vrstice"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only the options specific to &kleopatra; are listed here. As with all &kde; "
"applications, you can get a complete list of options by issuing the command "
"<userinput><command>kleopatra <option>--help</option></command></userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Samo možnosti, specifične za program &kleopatra; so navedene tukaj. Kot pri "
"vseh &kde; aplikacijah, lahko dobite celoten seznam možnosti z izdajo ukaza "
"<userinput><command>kleopatra <option>--help</option></command></userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1406
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--uiserver-socket</option> <replaceable>argument</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>--uiserver-socket</option> <replaceable>argument</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1408
#, no-c-format
msgid "Location of the socket the ui server is listening on"
msgstr "Lokacija vtičnice, ki jo strežnik uporabniškega vmesnika posluša"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1413
#, no-c-format
msgid "--daemon"
msgstr "--daemon"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1415
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run UI server only, hide main window"
msgstr "Zaženi samo strežnik UI, skrij glavno okno"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1420
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-p</option> <option>--openpgp</option>"
msgstr "<option>-p</option> <option>--openpgp</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1422
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use &openpgp; for the following operation"
msgstr "Uporabite &openpgp; za naslednjo operacijo"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1427
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-c</option> <option>--cms</option>"
msgstr "<option>-c</option> <option>--cms</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1429
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use CMS (&x509;, S/&MIME;) for the following operation"
msgstr "Uporabite CMS (&x509;, S/&MIME;) za naslednjo operacijo"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1434
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-i</option> <option>--import-certificate</option>"
msgstr "<option>-i</option> <option>--import-certificate</option>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:1436
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies a file or &URL; from which to import certificates (or secret keys) "
"from."
msgstr ""
"Določa datoteko ali &URL; iz katerega uvozite potrdila (ali tajne ključe)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1439
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the command line equivalent of <xref linkend=\"file-import-"
"certificates\"/>."
msgstr ""
"To je ekvivalent ukazne vrstice <xref linkend=\"file-import-certificates\"/>."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1445
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-e</option> <option>--encrypt</option>"
msgstr "<option>-e</option> <option>--encrypt</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1447
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encrypt file(s)"
msgstr "Šifriraj datoteko(e)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1452
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-s</option> <option>--sign</option>"
msgstr "<option>-s</option> <option>--sign</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1454
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sign file(s)"
msgstr "Podpiši datoteko(e)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1459
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-E</option> <option>--encrypt-sign</option>"
msgstr "<option>-E</option> <option>--encrypt-sign</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Encrypt and/or sign file(s). Same as <option>--sign-encrypt</option>, do not "
"use"
msgstr ""
"Šifrirajte in/ali podpišite datoteko(e). Enako kot <option>--sign-encrypt</"
"option>, ne uporabljajte"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1466
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-d</option> <option>--decrypt</option>"
msgstr "<option>-d</option> <option>--decrypt</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1468
#, no-c-format
msgid "Decrypt file(s)"
msgstr "Dešifriranje datotek(e)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1473
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-V</option> <option>--verify</option>"
msgstr "<option>-V</option> <option>--verify</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1475
#, no-c-format
msgid "Verify file/signature"
msgstr "Preveri datoteko/podpis"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1480
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-D</option> <option>--decrypt-verify</option>"
msgstr "<option>-D</option> <option>--decrypt-verify</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1482
#, no-c-format
msgid "Decrypt and/or verify file(s)"
msgstr "Dešifriranje in/ali preverjanje datotek"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1491
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring &kleopatra;"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje programa &kleopatra;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1493
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra;'s configure dialog can be accessed via "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure &kleopatra;..."
"</guimenuitem></menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"Do pogovornega okna za konfiguracijo programa &kleopatra; lahko dostopate "
"preko <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj "
"program &kleopatra;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1501
#, no-c-format
msgid "Each of its pages is described in the sections below."
msgstr "Vsaka njegova stran je opisana v spodnjih razdelkih."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1506
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Directory Services"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje imeniških storitev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1508
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On this page, you can configure which &ldap; servers to use for &smime; "
"certificate searches, and which key servers to use for &openpgp; certificate "
"searches."
msgstr ""
"Na tej strani lahko konfigurirate, katere &ldap; strežnike uporabiti za "
"&smime; iskanja potrdil in katere strežnike ključev uporabiti za &openpgp; "
"iskanja certifikatov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1514
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is simply a more user-friendly version of the same settings you also "
"find in <xref linkend=\"configuration-gnupg-system\"/>. Everything you can "
"configure here, you can configure there, too."
msgstr ""
"To je preprosto uporabniku prijaznejša različica istih nastavitev, ki jih "
"najdete tudi v <xref linkend=\"configuration-gnupg-system\"/>. Vse, kar "
"lahko konfigurirate tukaj, lahko konfigurirate tudi tam."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1522
#, no-c-format
msgid "A Note On Proxy Settings"
msgstr "Opomba o nastavitvah proxy strežnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1523
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Proxy settings can be configured for &http; and &ldap; in <xref linkend="
"\"configuration-smime-validation\"/>, but only for &gpgsm;. For &gpg;, due "
"to the complexity of keyserver options in &gpg; and lack of proper support "
"for them in &gpgconf;, you currently need to modify the config file "
"<filename>gpg.conf</filename> directly. Please refer to the &gpg; manual for "
"details. &kleopatra; will preserve such settings, but does not yet allow to "
"modify them in the &GUI;."
msgstr ""
"Nastavitve proxyja je mogoče konfigurirati za &http; in &ldap; v <xref "
"linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation\"/>, vendar samo za &gpgsm;. Za "
"&gpg; zaradi zapletenosti možnosti strežnika ključev v &gpg; in pomanjkanje "
"ustrezne podpore zanje v &gpgconf;, morate trenutno neposredno spremeniti "
"konfiguracijsko datoteko <filename>gpg.conf</filename>. Glejte &gpg; "
"priročnik za podrobnosti. Program &kleopatra; bo ohranil takšne nastavitve, "
"vendar še ne dovoljuje njihovega spreminjanja v &GUI;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Directory services</guilabel> table shows which servers are "
"currently configured. Double-click on a cell in the table to change "
"parameters of existing server entries."
msgstr ""
"The <guilabel>Directory services</guilabel> table shows which servers are "
"currently configured. Double-click on a cell in the table to change "
"parameters of existing server entries."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1539
#, no-c-format
msgid "The meaning of the columns in the table is as follows:"
msgstr "Pomen stolpcev v tabeli je naslednji:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1544
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scheme"
msgstr "Shema"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1546
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Determines the network protocol which is used to access the server. Often-"
"used schemes include <guilabel>ldap</guilabel> (and its &ssl;-secured "
"sibling <guilabel>ldaps</guilabel>) for &ldap; servers (common protocol for "
"&smime;; the only one supported by &gpgsm;), and <guilabel>hkp</guilabel>, "
"the Horowitz Keyserver Protocol, nowadays usually &http; Keyserver Protocol, "
"a &http;-based protocol that virtually all public &openpgp; keyservers "
"support."
msgstr ""
"Določa omrežni protokol, ki se uporablja za dostop do strežnika. Pogosto "
"uporabljene sheme vključujejo <guilabel>ldap</guilabel> (in njegov z &ssl; "
"zavarovanim brat <guilabel>ldaps</guilabel>) za &ldap; strežnike (skupni "
"protokol za &smime;; edini, ki ga podpira &gpgsm;), in <guilabel>hkp</"
"guilabel>, protokol strežnika ključev Horowitz, dandanes običajno &http; "
"Keyserver Protocol, protokol, ki temelji na &http; in ki skoraj vse javne "
"&openpgp; podpora za strežnike ključev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1557
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please refer to the &gpg; and &gpgsm; manuals for a list of supported "
"schemes."
msgstr "Glejte &gpg; in &gpgsm; priročniki za seznam podprtih shem."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1564
#, no-c-format
msgid "Server Name"
msgstr "Ime strežnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1566
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The domain name of the server, &eg; <systemitem class=\"systemname\">keys."
"gnupg.net</systemitem>."
msgstr ""
"Ime domene strežnika, npr. <systemitem class=\"systemname\">keys.gnupg.net</"
"systemitem>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1573
#, no-c-format
msgid "Server Port"
msgstr "Vrata strežnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1575
#, no-c-format
msgid "The network port the server is listening on."
msgstr "Omrežna vrata, ki jih strežnik posluša."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1578
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This changes automatically to the default port when you change the <xref "
"linkend=\"configuration-directory-services-scheme\"/>, unless it was set to "
"some non-standard port to begin with. If you changed the default port and "
"cannot get it back, try setting <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-"
"services-scheme\"/> to <userinput>http</userinput> and <xref linkend="
"\"configuration-directory-services-server-port\"/> to <userinput>80</"
"userinput> (the default for &http;), then take it from there."
msgstr ""
"To se samodejno spremeni v privzeta vrata, ko spremenite <xref linkend="
"\"configuration-directory-services-scheme\"/>, razen če so bila na začetku "
"nastavljena na nekatera nestandardna vrata. Če ste spremenili privzeta vrata "
"in jih ne morete obnoviti, poskusite <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-"
"services-scheme\"/> nastaviti na <userinput>http</userinput> in <xref "
"linkend=\"configuration-directory-services-server-port\"/> na <userinput>80</"
"userinput> (privzeto za &http;), nato pa ga vzemite od tam."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1594
#, no-c-format
msgid "Base DN"
msgstr "Osnovni DN"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1596
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Base-&dn; (only for &ldap; and &ldaps;), &ie; the root of the &ldap; "
"hierarchy to start from. This is often also called <quote>search root</"
"quote> or <quote>search base</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Osnovni DN (samo za &ldap; in &ldaps;), npr. koren &ldap; hierarhije, iz "
"katere je treba začeti. To se pogosto imenuje tudi <quote>iskalni koren</"
"quote> ali <quote>iskalna osnova</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1602
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It usually looks like <userinput>c=de,o=Foo</userinput>, given as part of "
"the &ldap; &URL;."
msgstr ""
"Običajno je videti kot <userinput>c=de,o=Foo</userinput>, podan kot del "
"datoteke &ldap; &URL;."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1609
#, no-c-format
msgid "User Name"
msgstr "Uporabniško ime"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1611
#, no-c-format
msgid "The user name, if any, to use for logging into the server."
msgstr "Uporabniško ime, če obstaja, za prijavo v strežnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1615 index.docbook:1629
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This column is only shown if the option <guilabel>Show user and password "
"information</guilabel> (below the table) is checked."
msgstr ""
"Ta stolpec je prikazan le, če je označena možnost <guilabel>Pokaži podatke o "
"uporabniku in geslu</guilabel> (pod tabelo)."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1623
#, no-c-format
msgid "Password"
msgstr "Geslo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1625
#, no-c-format
msgid "The password, if any, to use for logging into the server."
msgstr "Geslo, če obstaja, za prijavo v strežnik."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1637
#, no-c-format
msgid "X.509"
msgstr "X.509"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1639
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check this column if this entry should be used for &x509; (&smime;) "
"certificate searches."
msgstr ""
"Preverite ta stolpec, če naj se ta vnos uporabi za &x509; (&smime;) iskanja "
"potrdil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1643
#, no-c-format
msgid "Only &ldap; (and &ldaps;) servers are supported for &smime;."
msgstr "Samo &ldap; (in &ldaps;) strežniki so podprti za &smime;."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1650
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>OpenPGP</guilabel>"
msgstr "<guilabel>OpenPGP</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1652
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check this column if this entry should be used for &openpgp; certificate "
"searches."
msgstr ""
"Preverite ta stolpec, če naj se ta vnos uporabi za &openpgp; iskanje "
"certifikatov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can configure as many &smime; (&x509;) servers as you want, but only one "
"&openpgp; server is allowed at any time. The &GUI; will enforce this."
msgstr ""
"Konfigurirate lahko poljubno število &smime; (&x509;) strežnikov, kot "
"želite, vendar samo en &openpgp; strežnik je dovoljen kadar koli. &GUI; bo "
"to uveljavil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add a new server, click on the <guibutton>New</guibutton> button. This "
"duplicates the selected entry, if any, or else inserts a default &openpgp; "
"server. Then you can set the <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-"
"services-server-name\"/>, the <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-"
"services-server-port\"/>, the <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-"
"services-base-dn\"/>, and the usual <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-"
"services-password\"/> and <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-services-"
"user-name\"/>, both of which are only needed if the server requires "
"authentication."
msgstr ""
"Če želite dodati nov strežnik, kliknite gumb <guibutton>Novo</guibutton>. To "
"podvoji izbrani vnos, če obstaja, ali pa vstavi privzeti &openpgp; strežnik. "
"Nato lahko nastavite <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-services-server-"
"name\"/>, <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-services-server-port\"/>, "
"<xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-services-base-dn\"/> in običajno "
"<xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-services-password\"/> in <xref "
"linkend=\"configuration-directory-services-user-name\"/>, oba sta potrebna "
"le, če strežnik zahteva avtentikacijo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1676
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To directly insert an entry for &x509; certificates, use "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>New</guimenu><guimenuitem>X.509</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>; use <menuchoice><guimenu>New</guimenu><guimenuitem>OpenPGP</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> for &openpgp;."
msgstr ""
"Če želite neposredno vnesti vnos za &x509; potrdila, uporabite "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Novo</guimenu><guimenuitem>X.509</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>; uporabite <menuchoice><guimenu>Novo</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>OpenPGP</guimenuitem></menuchoice> za &openpgp;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1684
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To remove a server from the search list, select it in the list, then press "
"the <guibutton>Delete</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Če želite odstraniti strežnik s seznama iskanja, ga izberite na seznamu in "
"pritisnite gumb <guibutton>Izbriši</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1693
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To set the &ldap; timeout, &ie; the maximum time the backend will wait for a "
"server to respond, simply use the corresponding input field labeled "
"<guilabel>LDAP timeout (minutes:seconds)</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Če želite nastaviti &ldap; časovno omejitev, npr. najdaljši čas, ki ga bo "
"zaledje čakalo na odgovor strežnika, preprosto uporabite ustrezno vnosno "
"polje z oznako <guilabel>Časovna omejitev LDAP (minute:sekunde)</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1699
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If one of your servers has a large database, so that even reasonable "
"searches like <userinput>Smith</userinput> hit the <guilabel>maximum number "
"of items returned by query</guilabel>, you might want to increase this "
"limit. You can find out easily if you hit the limit during a search, since a "
"dialog box will pop up in that case, telling you that the results have been "
"truncated."
msgstr ""
"Če ima eden od vaših strežnikov veliko podatkovno bazo, tako da celo razumna "
"iskanja, kot je <userinput>Smith</userinput>, dosežejo <guilabel>največje "
"število elementov, ki jih vrne poizvedba</guilabel>, boste morda želeli "
"povečati to omejitev. Preprosto lahko ugotovite, ali med iskanjem dosežete "
"mejo, saj se v tem primeru prikaže pogovorno okno, ki vam pove, da so bili "
"rezultati okrnjeni."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1709
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some servers may impose their own limits on the number of items returned "
"from a query. In this case, increasing the limit here will not result in "
"more returned items."
msgstr ""
"Nekateri strežniki lahko uvedejo lastne omejitve glede števila elementov, ki "
"jih vrne poizvedba. V tem primeru povečanje omejitve tukaj ne bo povzročilo "
"več vrnjenih artiklov."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1719
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Appearance"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje videza"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1722
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring <guilabel>Tooltips</guilabel>"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje <guilabel>Namigov orodij</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1724
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the main certificate list, &kleopatra; can show details about a "
"certificate in a tooltip. The information displayed is the same as in the "
"<guilabel>Overview</guilabel> tab of the <guilabel>Certificate Details</"
"guilabel> dialog. Tooltips, however, can be restricted to show only a subset "
"of information for a less verbose experience."
msgstr ""
"Na glavnem seznamu potrdil programa &kleopatra; lahko prikaže podrobnosti o "
"potrdilu v opisu orodja. Prikazane informacije so enake kot na zavihku "
"<guilabel>Pregled</guilabel> pogovornega okna <guilabel>Podrobnosti o "
"potrdilu</guilabel>. Namige orodij pa je mogoče omejiti tako, da prikazujejo "
"samo podnabor informacij za manj podrobno izkušnjo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1736
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Key-ID</guilabel> is <emphasis>always</emphasis> shown. This "
"is to ensure that tooltips for different certificates do, in fact, differ "
"(this is especially important if only <xref linkend=\"tooltips-validity\"/> "
"has been selected)."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Key-ID</guilabel> je <emphasis>vedno</emphasis> prikazan. To "
"zagotavlja, da se opisi orodij za različna potrdila dejansko razlikujejo (to "
"je še posebej pomembno, če je izbran samo <xref linkend=\"tooltips-validity"
"\"/>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1744
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can independently enable or disable the following information sets:"
msgstr "Neodvisno lahko omogočite ali onemogočite naslednje nize informacij:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1750
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show validity"
msgstr "Pokaži veljavnost"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1752
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows information about the validity of a certificate: its current status, "
"issuer-&dn; (&smime; only), expiry dates (if any) and certificate usage "
"flags."
msgstr ""
"Prikazuje informacije o veljavnosti potrdila: njegov trenutni status, "
"izdajatelj-&dn; (samo &smime;), datumi poteka (če obstajajo) in oznake "
"uporabe potrdila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1757 index.docbook:1786
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "Primer:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1759
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<!--\n"
"                  -->This certificate is currently valid.\n"
"<!--              -->Issuer:            CN=Test-ZS 7,O=Intevation GmbH,C=DE\n"
"<!--              -->Validity:          from 25.08.2009 10:42 through "
"19.10.2010 10:42\n"
"<!--              -->Certificate usage: Signing EMails and Files, Encrypting "
"EMails and Files\n"
"<!--              -->Key-ID:            DC9D9E43<!--\n"
"                  -->"
msgstr ""
"<!--\n"
"                  -->Ta certifikat je trenutno veljaven.\n"
"<!--              -->Izdajatelj:            CN=Test-ZS 7,O=Intevation GmbH,"
"C=DE\n"
"<!--              -->Veljavnost:          od 25.08.2009 10:42 do 19.10.2010 "
"10:42\n"
"<!--              -->Uporaba certifikata: Podpisovanje E-pošte in datotek, "
"kriptiranje E-pošte in datotek\n"
"<!--              -->ID-ključa:            DC9D9E43<!--\n"
"                  -->"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1764
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show owner information"
msgstr "Pokaži informacije o lastniku"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1766
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows information about the owner of the certificate: subject-&dn; (&smime; "
"only), user-IDs (including emails addresses) and ownertrust (&openpgp; only)."
msgstr ""
"Prikazuje informacije o lastniku potrdila: subject-&dn; (samo &smime;), ID-"
"ji uporabnikov (vključno z e-poštnimi naslovi) in zaupanje lastnika (samo "
"&openpgp;)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1771
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&openpgp; example: <programlisting><!--\n"
"                  -->User-ID:           Gpg4winUserA &lt;gpg4winusera@test."
"hq&gt;\n"
"<!--              -->Key-ID:            C6BF6664\n"
"<!--              -->Ownertrust:        ultimate<!--\n"
"                  --></programlisting> &smime; example:"
msgstr ""
"&openpgp; primer: <programlisting><!--\n"
"                  -->ID-uporabnika:           Gpg4winUserA &lt;"
"gpg4winusera@test.hq&gt;\n"
"<!--              -->ID-ključa:            C6BF6664\n"
"<!--              -->Zaupanje uporabnika:        ultimate<!--\n"
"                  --></programlisting> &smime; primer:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1775
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<!--\n"
"                  -->Subject:           CN=Gpg4winTestuserA,OU=Testlab,"
"O=Gpg4win Project,C=DE\n"
"<!--              -->a.k.a.:            Gpg4winUserA@test.hq\n"
"<!--              -->Key-ID:            DC9D9E43<!--\n"
"                  -->"
msgstr ""
"<!--\n"
"                  -->Subjekt:           CN=Gpg4winTestuserA,OU=Testlab,"
"O=Gpg4win Project,C=DE\n"
"<!--              -->a.k.a.:            Gpg4winUserA@test.hq\n"
"<!--              -->ID-ključa:            DC9D9E43<!--\n"
"                  -->"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1780
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show technical details"
msgstr "Prikaži tehnične podrobnosti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1782
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows technical information about the certificate: serial number (&smime; "
"only), type, fingerprint and storage location."
msgstr ""
"Prikazuje tehnične podatke o potrdilu: serijsko številko (samo &smime;), "
"vrsto, prstni odtis in mesto shranjevanja."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1788
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<!--\n"
"                  -->Serial Number:     27\n"
"<!--              -->Certificate type:  1,024-bit RSA (secret certificate "
"available)\n"
"<!--              -->Key-ID:            DC9D9E43\n"
"<!--              -->Fingerprint:       "
"854F62EEEBB41BFDD3BE05D124971E09DC9D9E43\n"
"<!--              -->Stored:            on this computer<!--\n"
"                  -->"
msgstr ""
"<!--\n"
"                  -->Serijaska številka:     27\n"
"<!--              -->Tip certifikata:  1,024-bit RSA (na voljo je skrivni "
"certifikat)\n"
"<!--              -->ID-ključa:            DC9D9E43\n"
"<!--              -->Prstni odtis:       "
"854F62EEEBB41BFDD3BE05D124971E09DC9D9E43\n"
"<!--              -->Shranjeno:            na tem računalniku<!--\n"
"                  -->"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1797
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring <guilabel>Certificate Categories</guilabel>"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje <guilabel>Kategorij potrdil</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1799
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; allows you to customize the appearance of certificates in the "
"list view. This includes showing a small icon, but you can also influence "
"the foreground (text) and background colors, as well as the font."
msgstr ""
"Program &kleopatra; omogoča prilagajanje videza potrdil v pogledu seznama. "
"To vključuje prikaz majhne ikone, lahko pa vplivate tudi na barve ospredja "
"(besedilo) in ozadja ter pisave."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1805
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each certificate category in the list is assigned a set of colors, an icon "
"(optional) and a font in which certificates from that category are "
"displayed. The category list also acts as a preview of the settings. "
"Categories can be freely defined by the administrator or the power user, see "
"<xref linkend=\"admin-key-filters\"/> in <xref linkend=\"admin\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Vsaki kategoriji potrdila na seznamu je dodeljen niz barv, ikona (neobvezno) "
"in pisava, v kateri so prikazana potrdila iz te kategorije. Seznam kategorij "
"deluje tudi kot predogled nastavitev. Kategorije lahko poljubno določi "
"skrbnik ali napredni uporabnik, glejte <xref linkend=\"admin-key-filters\"/> "
"v <xref linkend=\"admin\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To set or change the icon of a category, select it in the list, and press "
"the <guibutton>Set Icon...</guibutton> button. The standard &kde; icon "
"selection dialog will appear where you can select an existing icon from the "
"&kde; collection, or load a custom one."
msgstr ""
"Če želite nastaviti ali spremeniti ikono kategorije, jo izberite na seznamu "
"in pritisnite gumb <guibutton>Nastavi ikono...</guibutton>. Pojavila se bo "
"standardno &kde; pogovorno okno za izbiro ikone, kjer lahko izberete "
"obstoječo ikono iz okna &kde; zbirke ali naložite zbirko po meri."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1820
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To remove an icon again, you need to press the <guibutton>Default "
"Appearance</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Če želite znova odstraniti ikono, morate pritisniti gumb <guibutton>Privzeti "
"videz</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1824
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To change the text (&ie; foreground) color of a category, select it in the "
"list, and press the <guibutton>Set Text Color...</guibutton> button. The "
"standard &kde; color selection dialog will appear where you can select an "
"existing color or create a new one."
msgstr ""
"Če želite spremeniti barvo besedila (tj. ospredja) kategorije, jo izberite "
"na seznamu in pritisnite gumb <guibutton>Nastavi barvo besedila...</"
"guibutton>. Pojavilo se bo standardno &kde; pogovorno okno za izbiro barve, "
"kjer lahko izberete obstoječo barvo ali ustvarite novo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1831
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Changing the background color is done in the same way, just press "
"<guibutton>Set Background Color...</guibutton> instead."
msgstr ""
"Spreminjanje barve ozadja se izvede na enak način, namesto tega samo "
"pritisnite <guibutton>Nastavi barvo ozadja...</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1835
#, no-c-format
msgid "To change the font, you basically have two options:"
msgstr "Če želite spremeniti pisavo, imate v bistvu dve možnosti:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1840
#, no-c-format
msgid "Modify the standard font, used for all list views in &kde;."
msgstr ""
"Spremenite standardno pisavo, ki se uporablja za vse poglede seznamov v "
"&kde;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1846
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use a custom font."
msgstr "Uporabite pisavo po meri."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1851
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first option has the advantage that the font will follow whichever style "
"you choose &kde;-wide, whereas the latter gives you full control over the "
"font to use. The choice is yours."
msgstr ""
"Prva možnost ima to prednost, da bo pisava sledila izbranemu slogu v &kde;, "
"medtem ko vam slednja omogoča popoln nadzor nad uporabljeno pisavo. Izbira "
"je vaša."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1857
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use the modified standard font, select the category in the list, and "
"check or uncheck the font modifiers <guilabel>Italic</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Bold</guilabel>, and/or <guilabel>Strikeout</guilabel>. You can "
"immediately see the effect on the font in the category list."
msgstr ""
"Če želite uporabiti spremenjeno standardno pisavo, izberite kategorijo na "
"seznamu in označite ali počistite modifikatorje pisave <guilabel>Ležeče</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>Krepko</guilabel> in/ali <guilabel>Prečrtano</"
"guilabel> . Na seznamu kategorij lahko takoj vidite učinek na pisavo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1864
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use a custom font, press the <guibutton>Set Font...</guibutton> button. "
"The standard &kde; font selection dialog will appear where you can select "
"the new font."
msgstr ""
"Če želite uporabiti pisavo po meri, pritisnite gumb <guibutton>Nastavi "
"pisavo...</guibutton>. Prikaže standardno &kde; pogovorno okno za izbiro "
"pisave, kjer lahko izberete novo pisavo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can still use the font modifiers to change the custom font, just as for "
"modifying the standard font."
msgstr ""
"Še vedno lahko uporabite modifikatorje pisave za spreminjanje pisave po "
"meri, tako kot za spreminjanje standardne pisave."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1876
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To switch back to the standard font, you need to press the "
"<guibutton>Default Appearance</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Če želite preklopiti nazaj na standardno pisavo, morate pritisniti gumb "
"<guibutton>Privzeti videz</guibutton>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1884
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring <guilabel>DN-Attribute Order</guilabel>"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje <guilabel>Vrstni red atributov DN</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1886
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Although &dn;s are hierarchical, the order of the individual components "
"(called relative &dn;s (RDNs), or &dn; attributes) is not defined. The order "
"in which the attributes are shown is thus a matter of personal taste or "
"company policy, which is why it is configurable in &kleopatra;."
msgstr ""
"Čeprav so &dn;-ji hierarhični, vrstni red posameznih komponent (imenovanih "
"relativni &dn;-ji (RDN) ali &dn; atributi) ni definiran. Vrstni red, v "
"katerem so prikazani atributi, je torej stvar osebnega okusa ali politike "
"podjetja, zato ga je mogoče konfigurirati v programu &kleopatra;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1892
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This setting does not only apply to &kleopatra;, but to all applications "
"using &kleopatra; Technology. At the time of this writing, these include "
"&kmail;, &kaddressbook;, as well as &kleopatra; itself, of course."
msgstr ""
"Ta nastavitev ne velja le za program &kleopatra;, ampak za vse aplikacije, "
"ki uporabljajo &kleopatra; tehnologijo. V času tega pisanja to vključuje "
"&kmail;, &kaddressbook;, kot tudi sama sebe, seveda."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1897
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This configuration page basically consists of two lists, one for the known "
"attributes (<guilabel>Available attributes</guilabel>), and one describing "
"the <guilabel>Current attribute order</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Ta konfiguracijska stran je v bistvu sestavljena iz dveh seznamov, enega za "
"znane atribute (<guilabel>Razpoložljivi atributi</guilabel>) in enega, ki "
"opisuje <guilabel>Trenutni vrstni red atributov</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1901
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Both lists contain entries described by the short form of the attribute "
"(&eg; <guilabel>CN</guilabel>) as well as the spelled-out form "
"(<guilabel>Common Name</guilabel>)."
msgstr ""
"Oba seznama vsebujeta vnose, opisane s kratko obliko atributa (npr. "
"<guilabel>CN</guilabel>) in črkovano obliko (<guilabel>Splošno ime</"
"guilabel>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1905
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Available attributes</guilabel> list is always sorted "
"alphabetically, while the <guilabel>Current attribute order</guilabel> "
"list's order reflects the configured &dn; attribute order: the first "
"attribute in the list is also the one displayed first."
msgstr ""
"Seznam <guilabel>Razpoložljivi atributi</guilabel> je vedno razvrščen po "
"abecedi, medtem ko vrstni red seznama <guilabel>Trenutni vrstni red "
"atributov</guilabel> odraža konfiguriran &dn; vrstni red atributov: prvi "
"atribut na seznamu je tudi prvi prikazan."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1911
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only attributes explicitly listed in the <guilabel>Current attribute order</"
"guilabel> list are displayed at all. The rest is hidden by default."
msgstr ""
"Sploh so prikazani samo atributi, ki so izrecno navedeni na seznamu "
"<guilabel>Trenutni vrstni red atributov</guilabel>. Ostalo je privzeto "
"skrito."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1915
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"However, if the placeholder entry <guilabel>_X_</guilabel> (<guilabel>All "
"others</guilabel>) is in the <quote>current</quote> list, all unlisted "
"attributes (whether known or not), are inserted at the point of "
"<guilabel>_X_</guilabel>, in their original relative order."
msgstr ""
"Vendar, če je vnos nadomestnega znaka <guilabel>_X_</guilabel> "
"(<guilabel>Vsi drugi</guilabel>) na <quote>trenutnem</quote> seznamu, so "
"vstavljeni vsi neuvrščeni atributi (znani ali ne) na točko kjer se nahaja "
"<guilabel>_X_</guilabel>, v njihovem izvirnem relativnem vrstnem redu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1921
#, no-c-format
msgid "A small example will help to make this more clear:"
msgstr "Majhen primer bo pomagal, da bo to bolj jasno:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1924
#, no-c-format
msgid "Given the &dn;"
msgstr "Glede na &dn;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1926
#, no-c-format
msgid "O=&kde;, C=US, CN=Dave Devel, X-BAR=foo, OU=&kleopatra;, X-FOO=bar,"
msgstr "O=&kde;, C=US, CN=Dave Devel, X-BAR=foo, OU=&kleopatra;, X-FOO=bar,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1930
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"the default attribute order of <quote>CN, L, _X_, OU, O, C</quote> will "
"produce the following formatted &dn;:"
msgstr ""
"privzeti vrstni red atributov <quote>CN, L, _X_, OU, O, C</quote> bo "
"ustvaril naslednje oblikovano &dn;:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1933
#, no-c-format
msgid "CN=Dave Devel, X-BAR=foo, X-FOO=bar, OU=&kleopatra;, O=&kde;, C=US"
msgstr "CN=Dave Devel, X-BAR=foo, X-FOO=bar, OU=&kleopatra;, O=&kde;, C=US"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1937
#, no-c-format
msgid "while <quote>CN, L, OU, O, C</quote> will produce"
msgstr "medtem ko bo <quote>CN, L, OU, O, C</quote> ustvaril"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1939
#, no-c-format
msgid "CN=Dave Devel, OU=&kleopatra;, O=&kde;, C=US"
msgstr "CN=Dave Devel, OU=&kleopatra;, O=&kde;, C=US"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1945
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add an attribute to the display order list, select it in the "
"<guilabel>Available attributes</guilabel> list, and press the <guilabel>Add "
"to current attribute order</guilabel> button."
msgstr ""
"Če želite dodati atribut na seznam vrstnega reda prikaza, ga izberite na "
"seznamu <guilabel>Razpoložljivi atributi</guilabel> in pritisnite gumb "
"<guilabel>Dodaj v trenutni vrstni red atributov</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1949
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To remove an attribute from the display order list, select it in the "
"<guilabel>Current attribute order</guilabel> list, and press the "
"<guilabel>Remove from current attribute order</guilabel> button."
msgstr ""
"Če želite odstraniti atribut s seznama vrstnega reda prikaza, ga izberite na "
"seznamu <guilabel>Trenutni vrstni red atributov</guilabel> in pritisnite "
"gumb <guilabel>Odstrani iz trenutnega vrstnega reda atributov</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1953
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To move an attribute to the beginning (end), select it in the "
"<guilabel>Current attribute order</guilabel> list, and press the "
"<guilabel>Move to top</guilabel> (<guilabel>Move to bottom</guilabel>) "
"button."
msgstr ""
"Če želite premakniti atribut na začetek (konec), ga izberite na seznamu "
"<guilabel>Trenutni vrstni red atributov</guilabel> in pritisnite "
"gumb<guilabel>Premakni na vrh</guilabel> (<guilabel>Premakni na dno</"
"guilabel>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1958
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To move an attribute up (down) one slot only, select it in the "
"<guilabel>Current attribute order</guilabel> list, and press the "
"<guilabel>Move one up</guilabel> (<guilabel>Move one down</guilabel>) button."
msgstr ""
"Če želite premakniti atribut gor (dol) samo za eno režo, ga izberite na "
"seznamu <guilabel>Trenutni vrstni red atributov</guilabel> in pritisnite "
"gumb<guilabel>Premakni enega gor</guilabel> (<guilabel>Premakni enega "
"navzdol</guilabel>)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1968
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Crypto Operations"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje kripto operacij"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1971
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring <guilabel>EMail Operations</guilabel>"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje <guilabel>E-poštnih operacij</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1973
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can configure some aspects of the email operations of &kleopatra;'s "
"&uiserver;. Currently, you can only configure whether or not to use "
"<quote>Quick Mode</quote> for signing and encrypting emails, individually."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj lahko konfigurirate nekatere vidike e-poštnih operacij kleopatrinega "
"&uiserver;ja. Trenutno lahko samo konfigurirate, ali želite uporabiti "
"<quote>Hitri način</quote> za posamično podpisovanje in šifriranje e-pošte."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1979
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When <quote>Quick Mode</quote> is enabled, no dialog is shown when signing "
"(encrypting) emails, respectively, unless there is a conflict that needs "
"manual resolution."
msgstr ""
"Ko je omogočen <quote>Hitri način</quote>, pri podpisovanju (šifriranju) e-"
"poštnih sporočil ni prikazano nobeno pogovorno okno, razen če obstaja spor, "
"ki ga je treba ročno razrešiti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1988
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring <guilabel>File Operations</guilabel>"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje <guilabel>datotečnih operacij</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1990
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can configure some aspects of the file operations of &kleopatra;'s "
"&uiserver;. Currently, you can only choose the checksum program to use for "
"<command>CHECKSUM_CREATE_FILES</command>."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj lahko konfigurirate nekatere vidike datotečnih operacij kleopatrinega "
"&uiserver;ja. Trenutno lahko izberete samo program kontrolne vsote za "
"<command>CHECKSUM_CREATE_FILES</command>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1996
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use <guilabel>Checksum program to use</guilabel> to choose which of the "
"configured checksum programs should be used when creating checksum files."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite <guilabel>Program kontrolne vsote za uporabo</guilabel>, da "
"izberete, kateri od nastavljenih programov kontrolne vsote naj bo uporabljen "
"pri ustvarjanju datotek kontrolne vsote."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2001
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When verifying checksums, the program to use is automatically found, based "
"on the names of the checksum files found."
msgstr ""
"Pri preverjanju kontrolnih vsot se samodejno najde program za uporabo na "
"podlagi imen najdenih datotek s kontrolnimi vsotami."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2007
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The administrator and power user can completely define which checksum "
"programs to make available to &kleopatra; through so-called <quote>Checksum "
"Definitions</quote> in the config file. See <xref linkend=\"admin-checksum-"
"definitions\"/> in <xref linkend=\"admin\"/> for details."
msgstr ""
"Skrbnik in izkušeni uporabnik lahko popolnoma določita, kateri programi za "
"kontrolne vsote naj bodo na voljo programu &kleopatra; prek tako imenovanih "
"<quote>Definicij kontrolne vsote</quote> v konfiguracijski datoteki. Za "
"podrobnosti glejte <xref linkend=\"admin-checksum-definitions\"/> v <xref "
"linkend=\"admin\"/>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2023
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring aspects of S/&MIME; Validation"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje vidikov S/&MIME; Validacije"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2025
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On this page, you can configure certain aspects of the validation of &smime; "
"certificates."
msgstr ""
"Na tej strani lahko konfigurirate nekatere vidike preverjanja &smime; "
"potrdila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2030
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For the most part, this is simply a more user-friendly version of the same "
"settings you also find in <xref linkend=\"configuration-gnupg-system\"/>. "
"Everything you can configure here, you can configure there, too, with the "
"exception of <xref linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation-refresh-interval"
"\"/>, which is &kleopatra;-specific."
msgstr ""
"Večinoma je to preprosto uporabniku prijaznejša različica istih nastavitev, "
"ki jih najdete tudi v <xref linkend=\"configuration-gnupg-system\"/>. Vse, "
"kar lahko konfigurirate tukaj, lahko konfigurirate tudi tam, z izjemo <xref "
"linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation-refresh-interval\"/>, ki je "
"specifičen za program &kleopatra;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2040
#, no-c-format
msgid "The meaning of the options is as follows:"
msgstr "Pomen možnosti je naslednji:"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2045
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring interval certificate checking"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje intervalnega preverjanja potrdila"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2049
#, no-c-format
msgid "Check certificate validity every <replaceable>N</replaceable> hours"
msgstr "Preverite veljavnost potrdila vsakih <replaceable>N</replaceable> ur"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2052
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option enables interval checking of certificate validity. You can also "
"choose the checking interval (in hours). The effect of interval checking is "
"the same as <xref linkend=\"view-redisplay\"/>; there is no provision for "
"interval scheduling of <xref linkend=\"certificates-refresh-openpgp\"/> or "
"<xref linkend=\"certificates-refresh-x509\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Ta možnost omogoča intervalno preverjanje veljavnosti certifikata. Izberete "
"lahko tudi interval preverjanja (v urah). Učinek intervalnega preverjanja je "
"enak kot <xref linkend=\"view-redisplay\"/>; ni možnosti za intervalno "
"razporejanje <xref linkend=\"certificates-refresh-openpgp\"/> ali <xref "
"linkend=\"certificates-refresh-x509\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2062
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Validation is performed implicitly whenever significant files in "
"<filename>~/.gnupg</filename> change. This option, just like <xref linkend="
"\"certificates-refresh-openpgp\"/> and <xref linkend=\"certificates-refresh-"
"x509\"/>, therefore only affects external factors of certificate validity."
msgstr ""
"Preverjanje veljavnosti se izvaja implicitno vsakič, ko se pomembne datoteke "
"v <filename>~/.gnupg</filename> spremenijo. Ta možnost, podobno kot <xref "
"linkend=\"certificates-refresh-openpgp\"/> in <xref linkend=\"certificates-"
"refresh-x509\"/>, torej vpliva le na zunanje dejavnike veljavnosti potrdila."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2077
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring validation method"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje metode preverjanja"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2081
#, no-c-format
msgid "Validate certificates using CRLs"
msgstr "Preverjanje potrdil z uporabo CRL-jev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2083
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is selected, &smime; certificates are validated using "
"Certificate Revocation Lists (&crl;s)."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta možnost izbrana, so &smime; potrdila potrjena s seznami preklicanih "
"potrdil (&crl;ji)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2087
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See <xref linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation-use-ocsp\"/> for "
"alternative method of certificate validity checking."
msgstr ""
"Glejte <xref linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation-use-ocsp\"/> za "
"alternativni način preverjanja veljavnosti potrdila."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2094
#, no-c-format
msgid "Validate certificates online (OCSP)"
msgstr "Potrdi potrdila na spletu (OCSP)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2096
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is selected, &smime; certificates are validated online using "
"the Online Certificates Status Protocol (&ocsp;)."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta možnost izbrana, se &smime; potrdila preverjajo na spletu s "
"protokolom o statusu spletnih potrdil (&ocsp;)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When choosing this method, a request is sent to the server of the &ca; more "
"or less each time you send or receive a cryptographic message, thus "
"theoretically allowing the certificate issuing agency to track whom you "
"exchange (&eg;) mails with."
msgstr ""
"Pri izbiri te metode se zahteva pošlje strežniku &ca; bolj ali manj vsakič, "
"ko pošljete ali prejmete kriptografsko sporočilo, s čimer teoretično "
"omogočite agenciji za izdajo potrdil, da sledi, s kom izmenjujete (npr.) "
"pošto."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use this method, you need to enter the &URL; of the &ocsp; responder into "
"<xref linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation-ocsp-url\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Če želite uporabiti to metodo, morate vnesti &URL; od &ocsp; odzivnika v "
"<xref linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation-ocsp-url\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See <xref linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation-use-ocsp\"/> for a more "
"traditional method of certificate validity checking that does not leak "
"information about whom you exchange messages with."
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si <xref linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation-use-ocsp\"/> za "
"bolj tradicionalno metodo preverjanja veljavnosti potrdila, ki ne razkrije "
"informacij o tem, s kom izmenjujete sporočila."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2123
#, no-c-format
msgid "OCSP responder URL"
msgstr "URL odzivnika OCSP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter here the address of the server for online validation of certificates "
"(&ocsp; responder). The &URL; usually starts with <literal>http://</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj vnesite naslov strežnika za spletno preverjanje potrdil (&ocsp; "
"odzivnik). &URL; se običajno začne z <literal>http://</literal>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2133
#, no-c-format
msgid "OCSP responder signature"
msgstr "Podpis odzivnika OCSP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose here the certificate with which the &ocsp; server signs its replies."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj izberite potrdilo, s katerim &ocsp; strežnik podpiše svoje odgovore."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2142
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore service URL of certificates"
msgstr "Prezri storitveni URL potrdil"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each &smime; certificate usually contains the &URL; of its issuer's &ocsp; "
"responder (<xref linkend=\"certificates-dump-certificate\"/> will reveal "
"whether a given certificate contains it)."
msgstr ""
"Vsako &smime; potrdilo običajno vsebuje &URL; njegovega izdajatelja &ocsp; "
"odzivnik (<xref linkend=\"certificates-dump-certificate\"/> bo razkril, ali "
"ga dano potrdilo vsebuje)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2150
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Checking this option makes &gpgsm; ignore those &URL;s and only use the one "
"configured above."
msgstr ""
"Če označite to možnost, bo &gpgsm; ignoriral te &URL;je in uporabljal samo "
"tistega, ki je konfiguriran zgoraj."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2154
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use this to &eg; enforce use of a company-wide &ocsp; proxy."
msgstr "Uporabite to za npr. uveljaviti uporabo &ocsp; zastopnika."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2166
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring validation options"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje možnosti preverjanja"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2170
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not check certificate policies"
msgstr "Ne preverjajte pravilnikov o potrdilih"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, &gpgsm; uses the file <filename>~/.gnupg/policies.txt</filename> "
"to check if a certificate policy is allowed. If this option is selected, "
"policies are not checked."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto je da &gpgsm; uporablja datoteko <filename>~/.gnupg/policies.txt</"
"filename> za preverjanje, ali je pravilnik o potrdilu dovoljen. Če je ta "
"možnost izbrana, pravilniki niso označeni."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2181
#, no-c-format
msgid "Never consult a CRL"
msgstr "Nikoli se ne posvetuj s CRL"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is checked, Certificate Revocation Lists are never used to "
"validate &smime; certificates."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta možnost označena, se seznami preklicanih potrdil nikoli ne "
"uporabijo za preverjanje &smime; potrdila."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2190
#, no-c-format
msgid "Allow to mark root certificates as trusted"
msgstr "Dovoli označevanje korenskih potrdil kot zaupanja vrednih"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is checked while a root &ca; certificate is being imported, "
"you will be asked to confirm its fingerprint and to state whether or not you "
"consider this root certificate to be trusted."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta možnost označena, medtem ko se korensko &ca; potrdilo uvaža, boste "
"morali potrditi njegov prstni odtis in navesti, ali menite, da je to "
"korensko potrdilo zaupanja vredno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A root certificate needs to be trusted before the certificates it certified "
"become trusted, but lightly allowing trusted root certificates into your "
"certificate store will undermine the security of the system."
msgstr ""
"Korensko potrdilo mora biti zaupanja vredno, preden potrdila, ki jih je "
"potrdilo, postanejo zaupanja vredna, vendar lahkotno dovoljevanje zaupanja "
"vrednim korenskim potrdilom v vašo shrambo potrdil bo ogrozilo varnost "
"sistema."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enabling this functionality in the backend can lead to popups from "
"&pinentry; at inopportune times (&eg; when verifying signatures), and can "
"thus block unattended email processing. For that reason, and because it is "
"desirable to be able to <emphasis>distrust</emphasis> a trusted root "
"certificate again, &kleopatra; allows manual setting of trust using <xref "
"linkend=\"certificates-trust-root\"/> and <xref linkend=\"certificates-"
"distrust-root\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Omogočanje te funkcije v ozadju lahko povzroči pojavna okna &pinentry; ob "
"neprimernem času (npr. pri preverjanju podpisov) in lahko tako blokira "
"nenadzorovano obdelavo e-pošte. Iz tega razloga in ker je zaželeno, da lahko "
"ponovno <emphasis>ne zaupamo</emphasis> zaupanja vrednemu korenskemu "
"potrdilu, &kleopatra; omogoča ročno nastavitev zaupanja z uporabo <xref "
"linkend=\"certificates-trust-root\"/> in <xref linkend=\"certificates-"
"distrust-root\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2216
#, no-c-format
msgid "This setting here does not influence the &kleopatra; function."
msgstr "Ta nastavitev tukaj ne vpliva na funkcijo programa &kleopatra;."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2224
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fetch missing issuer certificates"
msgstr "Pridobite manjkajoča potrdila izdajatelja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2226
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is checked, missing issuer certificates are fetched when "
"necessary (this applies to both validation methods, &crl;s and &ocsp;)."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta možnost označena, se po potrebi pridobijo manjkajoča potrdila "
"izdajatelja (to velja za obe metodi preverjanja, &crl; in &ocsp;)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2238
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring &http; request options"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje &http; možnosti zahtevanja"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2242
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not perform any HTTP requests"
msgstr "Ne izvajajte nobenih zahtev HTTP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2244
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entirely disables the use of &http; for &smime;."
msgstr "Popolnoma onemogoči uporabo &http; za &smime;."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore HTTP CRL distribution point of certificates"
msgstr "Prezri distribucijsko točko potrdil HTTP CRL"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When looking for the location of a &crl;, the to-be-tested certificate "
"usually contains what are known as <quote>&crl; Distribution Point</quote> "
"(<acronym>DP</acronym>) entries, which are &URL;s describing the way to "
"access the &crl;. The first-found <acronym>DP</acronym> entry is used."
msgstr ""
"Ko iščete lokacijo &crl;, potrdilo ki ga je treba preizkusiti, običajno "
"vsebuje tisto, kar je znano kot <quote>&crl; vnosi distribucijske točke</"
"quote> (<acronym>DP</acronym>), ki so &URL;ji ki opisujejo način dostopa do "
"&crl;. Uporabljen je prvi najdeni vnos <acronym>DP</acronym>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With this option, all entries using the &http; scheme are ignored when "
"looking for a suitable <acronym>DP</acronym>."
msgstr ""
"S to možnostjo se ne bodo vpošteali vsi vnosi, ki uporabljajo &http; shemo "
"pri iskanju ustreznega <acronym>DP</acronym>ja."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2268
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use system HTTP proxy"
msgstr "Uporabi sistemski proxy HTTP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2270
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is selected, the value of the &http; proxy shown on the right "
"(which comes from the environment variable <envar>http_proxy</envar>) will "
"be used for any &http; request."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta možnost izbrana, bo vrednost &http; proxy, prikazan na desni (ki "
"prihaja iz spremenljivke okolja <envar>http_proxy</envar>), uporabljena za "
"vse &http; prošnje."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2279
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use this proxy for HTTP requests"
msgstr "Uporabite ta proxy za zahteve HTTP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If no system proxy is set, or you need to use a different proxy for &gpgsm;, "
"you can enter its location here."
msgstr ""
"Če sistemski proxy ni nastavljen ali morate za &gpgsm; uporabiti drug proxy, "
"lahko tukaj vnesete njegovo lokacijo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2286
#, no-c-format
msgid "It will be used for all &HTTP; requests relating to S/&MIME;."
msgstr "Uporabljal se bo za vse &HTTP; zahteve v zvezi s S/&MIME;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The syntax is <userinput><replaceable>host</replaceable><literal>:</"
"literal><replaceable>port</replaceable></userinput>, &eg; <userinput>myproxy."
"nowhere.com:3128</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Sintaksa je <userinput><replaceable>gostitelj</replaceable><literal>:</"
"literal><replaceable>vrata</replaceable></userinput>, npr. "
"<userinput>myproxy.nowhere.com:3128</userinput>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2302
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring &ldap; request options"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje &ldap; možnosti zahtevanja"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2306
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not perform any LDAP requests"
msgstr "Ne izvajajte nobenih zahtev LDAP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2308
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entirely disables the use of &ldap; for &smime;."
msgstr "Popolnoma onemogoči uporabo &ldap; za &smime;."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2314
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore LDAP CRL distribution point of certificates"
msgstr "Ignorirajte distribucijsko točko potrdil LDAP CRL"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2316
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When looking for the location of a &crl;, the to-be-tested certificate "
"usually contains what are known as \"&crl; Distribution Point"
"\" (<acronym>DP</acronym>) entries, which are &URL;s describing the way to "
"access the &crl;. The first found <acronym>DP</acronym> entry is used."
msgstr ""
"Ko iščete lokacijo &crl;, potrdilo, ki ga je treba preizkusiti, običajno "
"vsebuje tako imenovane vnose »&crl; vnosi distribucijske "
"točke« (<acronym>DP</acronym>), ki &URL; opisujejo pot do dostopa do &crl;. "
"Uporabljen je prvi najdeni vnos <acronym>DP</acronym>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With this option, all entries using the &ldap; scheme are ignored when "
"looking for a suitable <acronym>DP</acronym>."
msgstr ""
"S to možnostjo se ne bodo vpoštevali vsi vnosi, ki uporabljajo &ldap; sheme "
"pri iskanju ustreznega <acronym>DP</acronym>ja."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2332
#, no-c-format
msgid "Primary host for LDAP requests"
msgstr "Primarni gostitelj za zahteve LDAP"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Entering an &ldap; server here will make all &ldap; requests go to that "
"server first. More precisely, this setting overrides any specified "
"<replaceable>host</replaceable> and <replaceable>port</replaceable> part in "
"an &ldap; &URL; and will also be used if <replaceable>host</replaceable> and "
"<replaceable>port</replaceable> have been omitted from the &URL;."
msgstr ""
"Vnos &ldap; strežnika tukaj bo naredil to da gredo vse &ldap; zahteve "
"najprej na ta strežnik. Natančneje, ta nastavitev preglasi vse navedene "
"<replaceable>gostitelj</replaceable> in <replaceable>vrata</replaceable> "
"dele v &ldap; &URL;ju in bo uporabljen tudi, če sta <replaceable>gostitelj</"
"replaceable> in <replaceable>vrata</replaceable> izpuščena iz &URL;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2345
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Other &ldap; servers will be used only if the connection to the "
"<quote>proxy</quote> failed. The syntax is <userinput><replaceable>host</"
"replaceable></userinput> or <userinput><replaceable>host</"
"replaceable><literal>:</literal><replaceable>port</replaceable></userinput>. "
"If <replaceable>port</replaceable> is omitted, port 389 (standard &ldap; "
"port) is used."
msgstr ""
"Drugi &ldap; strežniki bodo uporabljeni le, če povezava s <quote>proxy</"
"quote> ni uspela. Sintaksa je <userinput><replaceable>gostitelj</"
"replaceable></userinput> ali <userinput><replaceable>gostitelj</"
"replaceable><literal>:</literal><replaceable>vrata</replaceable></"
"userinput> . Če so <replaceable>vrata</replaceable> izpuščena, se uporabijo "
"vrata 389 (standardna &ldap; vrata)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2366
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the &gnupg; System"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje &gnupg; sistema"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This part of the dialog is auto-generated from the output of "
"<command>gpgconf <option>--list-components</option></command> and, for each "
"<replaceable>component</replaceable> that the above command returns, the "
"output of <command>gpgconf <option>--list-options</option> "
"<replaceable>component</replaceable></command>."
msgstr ""
"Ta del pogovornega okna je samodejno ustvarjen iz izhoda <command>gpgconf "
"<option>--list-components</option></command> in za vsako "
"<replaceable>komponento</replaceable>, ki jo vrne zgornji ukaz , rezultat "
"<command>gpgconf <option>--list-options</option> <replaceable>komponenta</"
"replaceable></command>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2377
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most useful of these options have been duplicated as separate pages in "
"the &kleopatra; config dialog. See <xref linkend=\"configuration-directory-"
"services\"/> and <xref linkend=\"configuration-smime-validation\"/> for the "
"two dialog pages which contain selected options from this part of the dialog."
msgstr ""
"Najbolj uporabne od teh možnosti so bile podvojene kot ločene strani v "
"konfiguracijskem pogovornem oknu programa &kleopatra;. Oglejte si <xref "
"linkend=\"configuration-directory-services\"/> in <xref linkend="
"\"configuration-smime-validation\"/> za dve pogovorni strani, ki vsebujeta "
"izbrane možnosti iz tega dela pogovornega okna."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The exact content of this part of the dialog depends on the version of the "
"&gnupg; backend you have installed and, potentially, the platform you run "
"on. Thus, we will only discuss the general layout of the dialog, including "
"the mapping from &gpgconf; option to &kleopatra; &GUI; control."
msgstr ""
"Natančna vsebina tega dela pogovornega okna je odvisna od različice &gnupg; "
"ozadja, ki ste ga namestili, in potencialno platformo, na kateri delujete. "
"Tako bomo razpravljali le o splošni postavitvi pogovornega okna, vključno s "
"preslikavo iz &gpgconf; možnosti v &kleopatra; &GUI; nadzor."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2393
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&gpgconf; returns configuration information for multiple components. Inside "
"each component, individual options are combined into groups."
msgstr ""
"&gpgconf; vrne informacije o konfiguraciji za več komponent. Znotraj vsake "
"komponente so posamezne možnosti združene v skupine."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; displays one tab per component reported by &gpgconf;; groups are "
"headed by a horizontal line displaying the group name as returned from "
"&gpgconf;."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; prikaže en zavihek na komponento, ki jo poroča &gpgconf;; "
"skupine vodi s strani vodoravne črte, ki prikazuje ime skupine, vrnjeno iz "
"&gpgconf;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2403
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each &gpgconf; option has a type. Except for certain well-known options "
"which &kleopatra; backs with specialised controls for a better user "
"experience, the mapping between &gpgconf; types and &kleopatra; controls is "
"as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Vsaka &gpgconf; možnost ima vrsto. Razen nekaterih dobro znanih možnosti, ki "
"jih &kleopatra; podpira z specializiranimi kontrolami za boljšo uporabniško "
"izkušnjo, preslikavo med &gpgconf; vrstami in kontrolami kleopatre so "
"naslednje:"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2410
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mapping From &gpgconf; Types To &GUI; Controls"
msgstr "Preslikava iz &gpgconf; vrste v &GUI; kontrole"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2417
#, no-c-format
msgid "&gpgconf; type"
msgstr "tip &gpgconf;"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2418
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kleopatra; control"
msgstr "nadzor programa &kleopatra;"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2421
#, no-c-format
msgid "for lists"
msgstr "za sezname"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2422
#, no-c-format
msgid "for non-lists"
msgstr "za ne-sezname"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:2428
#, no-c-format
msgid "none"
msgstr "nobeden"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2429
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spinbox (<quote>count</quote>-semantics)"
msgstr "Spinbox (<quote>count</quote>-semantics)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2430
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checkbox"
msgstr "Potrditveno polje"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:2433
#, no-c-format
msgid "string"
msgstr "niz"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2434 index.docbook:2447 index.docbook:2453 index.docbook:2457
#, no-c-format
msgid "&NA;"
msgstr "&NA;"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2435
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lineedit"
msgstr "Lineedit"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:2438
#, no-c-format
msgid "int32"
msgstr "int32"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2439
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lineedit (unformatted)"
msgstr "Lineedit (neformatirano)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2440
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spinbox"
msgstr "Spinbox"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:2443
#, no-c-format
msgid "uint32"
msgstr "uint32"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:2446
#, no-c-format
msgid "pathname"
msgstr "ime poti"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2448 index.docbook:2452
#, no-c-format
msgid "specialised control"
msgstr "specializiran nadzor"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:2451
#, no-c-format
msgid "ldap server"
msgstr "ldap server"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:2456
#, no-c-format
msgid "key fingerprint"
msgstr "prstni odtis ključa"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:2460
#, no-c-format
msgid "pub key"
msgstr "javni ključ"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:2463
#, no-c-format
msgid "sec key"
msgstr "skrivni ključ"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:2466
#, no-c-format
msgid "alias list"
msgstr "seznam vzdevkov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2471
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See the &gpgconf; manual for more information about what you can configure "
"here, and how."
msgstr ""
"Glejte &gpgconf; priročnik za več informacij o tem, kaj lahko tukaj "
"konfigurirate in kako."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2480
#, no-c-format
msgid "Administrator's Guide"
msgstr "Vodnik za skrbnike"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This Administrator's Guide describes ways to customize &kleopatra; that are "
"not accessible via the &GUI;, but only via config files."
msgstr ""
"Ta vodnik za skrbnike opisuje načine prilagajanja programa &kleopatra; ki "
"niso dostopne prek &GUI;ja, ampak samo prek konfiguracijskih datotek."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2485
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is assumed that the reader is familiar with the technology used for &kde; "
"application configuration, including layout, file system location and "
"cascading of &kde; config files, as well as the KIOSK framework."
msgstr ""
"Predpostavlja se, da je bralec seznanjen s tehnologijo, ki se uporablja za "
"&kde; konfiguracijo aplikacije, vključno s postavitvijo, lokacijo "
"datotečnega sistema in kaskadnim povezovanjem &kde; konfiguracijske "
"datoteke, kot tudi ogrodje KIOSK."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2490
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customization of the Certificate-Creation Wizard"
msgstr "Prilagajanje čarovnika za ustvarjanje potrdila"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2492
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customizing the &dn; fields"
msgstr "Prilagajanje &dn; polj"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2494
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; allows you to customize the fields that the user is allowed to "
"enter in order to create their certificate."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; vam omogoča, da prilagodite polja, ki jih lahko uporabnik vnese, "
"da ustvari svoje potrdilo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2497
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a group called <literal>CertificateCreationWizard</literal> in the "
"system-wide <filename>kleopatrarc</filename>. If you want a custom order of "
"attributes or if you only want certain items to appear, create a key called "
"<varname>DNAttributeOrder</varname>. The argument is one or more of "
"<varname>CN,SN,GN,L,T,OU,O,PC,C,SP,DC,BC,EMAIL</varname> If you want to "
"initialize fields with a certain value, write something like "
"Attribute=value. If you want the attribute to be treated as a required one, "
"append an exclamation mark (e.g. <varname>CN!,L,OU,O!,C!,EMAIL!</varname>, "
"which happens to be the default configuration)."
msgstr ""
"Ustvarite skupino z imenom <literal>CertificateCreationWizard</literal> v "
"<filename>kleopatrarc</filename> celotnega sistema. Če želite vrstni red "
"atributov po meri ali če želite, da se prikažejo samo določeni elementi, "
"ustvarite ključ z imenom <varname>DNAttributeOrder</varname>. Argument je "
"eden ali več od <varname>CN,SN,GN,L,T,OU,O,PC,C,SP,DC,BC,EMAIL</varname> Če "
"želite inicializirati polja z določeno vrednostjo, napišite nekaj takega kot "
"Attribute=vrednost. Če želite, da se atribut obravnava kot obvezen, dodajte "
"klicaj (npr. <varname>CN!,L,OU,O!,C!,EMAIL!</varname>, kar je privzeta "
"konfiguracija) ."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2509
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the <acronym>KIOSK</acronym> mode modifier <varname>$e</varname> "
"allows to retrieve the values from environment variables or from an "
"evaluated script or binary. If you want to disallow editing of the "
"respective field in addition, use the modifier <varname>$i</varname>. If you "
"want to disallow the use <guibutton>Insert My Address</guibutton> button, "
"set <varname>ShowSetWhoAmI</varname> to false."
msgstr ""
"Uporaba modifikatorja načina <acronym>KIOSK</acronym> <varname>$e</varname> "
"omogoča pridobivanje vrednosti iz spremenljivk okolja ali iz ovrednotenega "
"skripta ali binarne datoteke. Če poleg tega želite onemogočiti urejanje "
"zadevnega polja, uporabite modifikator <varname>$i</varname>. Če želite "
"onemogočiti uporabo gumba <guibutton>Vstavi moj naslov</guibutton>, "
"nastavite <varname>ShowSetWhoAmI</varname> na false."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2517
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Due to the nature of the &kde; <acronym>KIOSK</acronym> framework, using the "
"immutable flag (<varname>$i</varname>) makes it impossible for the user to "
"override the flag. This is intended behavior. <varname>$i</varname> and "
"<varname>$e</varname> can be used with all other config keys in &kde; "
"applications as well."
msgstr ""
"Zaradi narave &kde; ogrodja <acronym>KIOSK</acronym> z uporabo "
"nespremenljive zastavice (<varname>$i</varname>) uporabniku onemogoča "
"preglasitev zastavice. To je predvideno vedenje. <varname>$i</varname> in "
"<varname>$e</varname> lahko uporabite z vsemi drugimi konfiguracijskimi "
"ključi v &kde;, tudi aplikacije."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2523
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following example outlines possible customizations:"
msgstr "Naslednji primer opisuje možne prilagoditve:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:2526
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"[CertificateCreationWizard]\n"
";Disallow to copy personal data from the addressbook, do not allow local "
"override\n"
"ShowSetWhoAmI[$i]=false\n"
"\n"
";sets the user name to $USER\n"
"CN[$e]=$USER\n"
"\n"
";sets the company name to \"My Company\", disallows editing\n"
"O[$i]=My Company\n"
"\n"
";sets the department name to a value returned by a script\n"
"OU[$ei]=$(lookup_dept_from_ip)\n"
"\n"
"; sets country to DE, but allows for changes by the user\n"
"C=DE"
msgstr ""
"[CertificateCreationWizard]\n"
";Prepove kopiranja osebnih podatkov iz imenika in lokalnega prepisovanja\n"
"ShowSetWhoAmI[$i]=false\n"
"\n"
";nastavi ime upoprabnika na $USER\n"
"CN[$e]=$USER\n"
"\n"
";nastavi ime podjetja na \"My Company\", prepove urejanje\n"
"O[$i]=My Company\n"
"\n"
";nastavi ime oddelka na vrednost vrnjeno iz skripta\n"
"OU[$ei]=$(lookup_dept_from_ip)\n"
"\n"
"; nastavi državo na DE, ampak dovoli spremembe s strani uporabnika\n"
"C=DE"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2533
#, no-c-format
msgid "Restricting the Types of Keys a User is Allowed to Create"
msgstr "Omejitev vrst ključev, ki jih uporabnik lahko ustvari"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2535
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; also allows to restrict which type of certificates a user is "
"allowed to create. Note, however, that an easy way around these restrictions "
"is to just create one on the command line."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; omogoča tudi omejitev vrste potrdil, ki jih uporabnik lahko "
"ustvari. Upoštevajte pa, da je tem omejitvam preprost način, da ustvarite "
"eno v ukazni vrstici."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2544
#, no-c-format
msgid "Public Key Algorithms"
msgstr "Algoritmi javnih ključev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2546
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To restrict the public key algorithm to use, add the config key "
"<varname>PGPKeyType</varname> (and <varname>CMSKeyType</varname>, but only "
"<acronym>RSA</acronym> is supported for <acronym>CMS</acronym> anyway) to "
"the <literal>CertificateCreationWizard</literal> section of "
"<filename>kleopatrarc</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Če želite omejiti uporabo algoritma javnega ključa, dodajte konfiguracijski "
"ključ <varname>PGPKeyType</varname> (in <varname>CMSKeyType</varname>, "
"vendar je za <acronym>CMS</acronym> vseeno podprt samo <acronym>RSA</"
"acronym>) v razdelek <literal>CertificateCreationWizard</literal> datoteke "
"<filename>kleopatrarc</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2556
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The allowed values are <literal>RSA</literal> for <acronym>RSA</acronym> "
"keys, <literal>DAS</literal> for <acronym>DSA</acronym> (sign-only) keys, "
"and <literal>DSA+ELG</literal> for a <acronym>DSA</acronym> (sign-only) key "
"with an Elgamal subkey for encryption."
msgstr ""
"Dovoljene vrednosti so <literal>RSA</literal> za ključe <acronym>RSA</"
"acronym>, <literal>DAS</literal> za ključe <acronym>DSA</acronym> (samo za "
"znak) in <literal >DSA+ELG</literal> za ključ <acronym>DSA</acronym> (samo "
"za znakovni ključ) s podključem Elgamal za šifriranje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2564
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default is read from &gpgconf; or else <literal>RSA</literal> if "
"&gpgconf; doesn't provide a default."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto je prebrano iz &gpgconf; ali drugače iz <literal>RSA</literal>, če "
"&gpgconf; ne zagotavlja privzete vrednosti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2574
#, no-c-format
msgid "Public Key Size"
msgstr "Velikost javnega ključa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2576
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To restrict the available keys sizes for a public algorithm, add the config "
"key <varname><replaceable>&lt;ALG&gt;</replaceable>KeySizes</varname> (where "
"<replaceable>ALG</replaceable> may be <literal>RSA</literal>, <literal>DSA</"
"literal> or <literal>ELG</literal>) to the "
"<literal>CertificateCreationWizard</literal> section of "
"<filename>kleopatrarc</filename>, containing a comma-separated list of "
"keysizes (in bits). A default may be indicated by prefixing the keysize with "
"a hyphen (<literal>-</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"Če želite omejiti razpoložljive velikosti ključev za javni algoritem, "
"dodajte konfiguracijski ključ <varname><replaceable>&lt;ALG&gt;</"
"replaceable>KeySizes</varname> (kjer je <replaceable>ALG</replaceable> lahko "
"<literal>RSA </literal>, <literal>DSA</literal> ali <literal>ELG</literal>) "
"v razdelek <literal>CertificateCreationWizard</literal> datoteke "
"<filename>kleopatrarc</filename>, ki vsebuje seznam, ločen z vejicami "
"velikosti ključev (v bitih). Privzeto vrednost lahko navedete tako, da pred "
"velikostjo ključa dodate vezaj (<literal>-</literal>)."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:2591
#, no-c-format
msgid "RSAKeySizes = 1536,-2048,3072"
msgstr "RSAKeySizes = 1536,-2048,3072"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2595
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The above would restrict allowed <acronym>RSA</acronym> key sizes to 1536, "
"2048 and 3072, with 2048 the default."
msgstr ""
"Zgornje bi omejilo dovoljene velikosti ključev <acronym>RSA</acronym> na "
"1536, 2048 in 3072, pri čemer je 2048 privzeto."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition to the sizes themselves, you may also specify labels for each of "
"the sizes. Simply set the config key <varname><replaceable>ALG</"
"replaceable>KeySizeLabels</varname> to a comma-separated list of labels."
msgstr ""
"Poleg samih velikosti lahko določite tudi oznake za vsako od velikosti. "
"Preprosto nastavite konfiguracijski ključ <varname><replaceable>ALG</"
"replaceable>KeySizeLabels</varname> na seznam oznak, ločenih z vejicami."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:2608
#, no-c-format
msgid "RSAKeySizeLabels = weak,normal,strong"
msgstr "RSAKeySizeLabels = šibek,normalen,močen"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2611
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The above, in connection with the previous example, would print something "
"like the following options for selection:"
msgstr ""
"Zgornje bi v povezavi s prejšnjim primerom natisnilo nekaj takega kot "
"naslednje možnosti za izbiro:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:2614
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"weak (1536 bits)\n"
"              normal (2048 bits)\n"
"              strong (3072 bits)"
msgstr ""
"šibek (1536 bits)\n"
"              normalen (2048 bits)\n"
"              močen (3072 bits)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2617
#, no-c-format
msgid "The defaults are as if the following was in effect:"
msgstr "Privzete vrednosti so, kot da bi veljalo naslednje:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:2619
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"RSAKeySizes = 1536,-2048,3072,4096\n"
"              RSAKeySizeLabels =\n"
"              DSAKeySizes = -1024,2048\n"
"              DSAKeySizeLabels = v1,v2\n"
"              ELGKeySizes = 1536,-2048,3072,4096"
msgstr ""
"RSAKeySizes = 1536,-2048,3072,4096\n"
"              RSAKeySizeLabels =\n"
"              DSAKeySizes = -1024,2048\n"
"              DSAKeySizeLabels = v1,v2\n"
"              ELGKeySizes = 1536,-2048,3072,4096"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2630
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating and Editing Key Categories"
msgstr "Ustvarjanje in urejanje ključnih kategorij"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2632
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; allows the user to configure the <link linkend=\"configuration-"
"appearance-certificate-filters\">visual appearance</link> of keys based on a "
"concept called <guilabel>Key Categories</guilabel>. <guilabel>Key "
"Categories</guilabel> are also used to filter the list of certificates. This "
"section describes how you can edit the available categories and add new ones."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; omogoča uporabniku, da konfigurira <link linkend=\"configuration-"
"appearance-certificate-filters\">vizualni videz</link> ključev na podlagi "
"koncepta, imenovanega <guilabel>Ključne kategorije</guilabel>. "
"<guilabel>Ključne kategorije</guilabel> se uporabljajo tudi za filtriranje "
"seznama potrdil. Ta razdelek opisuje, kako lahko uredite razpoložljive "
"kategorije in dodate nove."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2642
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When trying to find the category a key belongs to, &kleopatra; tries to "
"match the key to a sequence of key filters, configured in the "
"<filename>libkleopatrarc</filename>. The first one to match defines the "
"category, based on a concept of <emphasis>specificity</emphasis>, explained "
"further below."
msgstr ""
"Ko poskuša najti kategorijo, ki ji ključ pripada, &kleopatra; poskuša "
"uskladiti ključ z zaporedjem ključnih filtrov, konfiguriranih v "
"<filename>libkleopatrarc</filename>. Prvi, ki se ujema, definira kategorijo "
"na podlagi koncepta <emphasis>specifičnosti</emphasis>, ki je podrobneje "
"pojasnjen spodaj."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2650
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each key filter is defined in a config group named <literal>Key Filter "
"#<replaceable>n</replaceable></literal>, where <replaceable>n</replaceable> "
"is a number, starting from <literal>0</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Vsak ključni filter je definiran v konfiguracijski skupini z imenom "
"<literal>Key Filter #<replaceable>n</replaceable></literal>, kjer je "
"<replaceable>n</replaceable> število, ki se začne od <literal>0</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2657
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The only mandatory keys in a <literal>Key Filter #<replaceable>n</"
"replaceable></literal> group are <varname>Name</varname>, containing the "
"name of the category as displayed in the <link linkend=\"configuration-"
"appearance-certificate-filters\">config dialog</link>, and <varname>id</"
"varname>, which is used as a reference for the filter in other configuration "
"sections (such as <literal>View #<replaceable>n</replaceable></literal>)."
msgstr ""
"Edini obvezni ključi v skupini <literal>Key Filter #<replaceable>n</"
"replaceable></literal> so <varname>Ime</varname>, ki vsebuje ime kategorije, "
"kot je prikazano v <link linkend=\"configuration-appearance-certificate-"
"filters\">konfiguracijskem pogovornem oknu</link> in <varname>id</varname>, "
"ki se uporablja kot referenca za filter v drugih razdelkih konfiguracije "
"(kot je <literal>Pogled #<replaceable> n</replaceable></literal>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2668
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"lists all keys that define the display properties of keys belonging to that "
"category (&ie; those keys that can be adjusted in the <link linkend="
"\"configuration-appearance-certificate-filters\">config dialog</link>), "
"whereas <xref linkend=\"table-key-filters-criteria\"/> lists all keys that "
"define the criteria the filter matches keys against."
msgstr ""
"navaja vse ključe, ki določajo lastnosti prikaza ključev, ki pripadajo tej "
"kategoriji (tj. tiste ključe, ki jih je mogoče prilagoditi v <link linkend="
"\"configuration-appearance-certificate-filters\">konfiguracijskem pogovornem "
"oknu</link>), medtem ko <xref linkend=\"table-key-filters-criteria\"/> "
"navaja vse ključe, ki določajo kriterije, s katerimi se filter ujema s "
"ključi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2678
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key-Filter Configuration Keys Defining Display Properties"
msgstr "Ključi za konfiguracijo filtra ključev, ki določajo lastnosti zaslona"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2684 index.docbook:2764
#, no-c-format
msgid "Config Key"
msgstr "Konfiguracijski ključ"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2685 index.docbook:2765
#, no-c-format
msgid "Type"
msgstr "Tip"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2686
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Opis"

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2692
#, no-c-format
msgid "background-color"
msgstr "barva-ozadja"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2693 index.docbook:2702
#, no-c-format
msgid "color"
msgstr "barva"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2694
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The background color to use. If missing, defaults to whichever background "
"color is defined globally for list views."
msgstr ""
"Uporabljena barva ozadja. Če manjka, je privzeta barva ozadja, ki je "
"globalno definirana za poglede seznama."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2701
#, no-c-format
msgid "foreground-color"
msgstr "barva-ospredja"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2703
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The foreground color to use. If missing, defaults to whichever foreground "
"color is defined globally for list views."
msgstr ""
"Barva ospredja za uporabo. Če manjka, je privzeta barva ospredja, ki je "
"globalno definirana za poglede seznama."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2710
#, no-c-format
msgid "<varname>font</varname>"
msgstr "<varname>pisava</varname>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2711
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>font</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>pisava</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2712
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The custom font to use. The font will be scaled to the size configured for "
"list views, and any font attributes (see below) will be applied."
msgstr ""
"Uporabljena pisava po meri. Pisava bo pomanjšana na velikost, konfigurirano "
"za poglede seznama, uporabljeni pa bodo vsi atributi pisave (glejte spodaj)."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2719
#, no-c-format
msgid "font-bold"
msgstr "krepka-pisava"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2720 index.docbook:2731 index.docbook:2739 index.docbook:2773
#: index.docbook:2792 index.docbook:2797 index.docbook:2805 index.docbook:2813
#: index.docbook:2820 index.docbook:2827 index.docbook:2835 index.docbook:2843
#: index.docbook:2851 index.docbook:2859 index.docbook:2866 index.docbook:2874
#, no-c-format
msgid "boolean"
msgstr "boolean"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2721
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set to <literal>true</literal> and <varname>font</varname> is not set, "
"uses the default list view font with bold font style added (if available). "
"Ignored if <varname>font</varname> is also present."
msgstr ""
"Če je nastavljeno na <literal>true</literal> in <varname>pisava</varname> ni "
"nastavljena, uporablja privzeto pisavo pogleda seznama z dodanim krepkim "
"slogom pisave (če je na voljo). Prezrto, če je prisotna tudi "
"<varname>pisava</varname>."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2730
#, no-c-format
msgid "font-italic"
msgstr "poševna-pisava"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2732
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Analogous to <varname>font-bold</varname>, but for italic font style instead "
"of bold."
msgstr ""
"Podobno kot <varname>krepka-pisava</varname>, vendar za slog pisave ležeče "
"namesto krepko."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2738
#, no-c-format
msgid "font-strikeout"
msgstr "prečrtana-pisava"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2740
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <literal>true</literal>, draws a centered line over the font. Applied "
"even if <varname>font</varname> is set."
msgstr ""
"Če je <literal>true</literal>, nariše sredinsko črto čez pisavo. Uporabljeno "
"tudi, če je nastavljena <varname>pisava</varname>."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2747
#, no-c-format
msgid "icon"
msgstr "ikona"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2748
#, no-c-format
msgid "text"
msgstr "besedilo"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2749
#, no-c-format
msgid "The name of an icon to show in the first column. Not yet implemented."
msgstr "Ime ikone za prikaz v prvem stolpcu. Še ni implementirano."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2759
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key-Filter Configuration Keys Defining Filter Criteria"
msgstr "Ključi za konfiguracijo filtra ključev, ki določajo kriterije filtra"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2766
#, no-c-format
msgid "If specified, filter matches when..."
msgstr "Če je navedeno, se filter ujema, ko..."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2772
#, no-c-format
msgid "is-revoked"
msgstr "je-preklican"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2774
#, no-c-format
msgid "the key has been revoked."
msgstr "ključ je bil preklican."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2777
#, no-c-format
msgid "match-context"
msgstr "kontekst-ujemanja"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2778
#, no-c-format
msgid "context"
msgstr "kontekst"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2780
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Context is an enumeration with the following allowed values: "
"<literal>appearance</literal>, <literal>filtering</literal> and "
"<literal>any</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Kontekst je oštevilčenje z naslednjimi dovoljenimi vrednostmi: "
"<literal>videz</literal>, <literal>filtriranje</literal> in <literal>vsak</"
"literal>."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2788
#, no-c-format
msgid "the context in which this filter matches."
msgstr "kontekst, v katerem se ta filter ujema."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2791
#, no-c-format
msgid "is-expired"
msgstr "je-potekel"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2793
#, no-c-format
msgid "the key is expired."
msgstr "ključ je potekel."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2796
#, no-c-format
msgid "is-disabled"
msgstr "je-onemogočen"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2798
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"the key has been disabled (marked for not using) by the user. Ignored for "
"&smime; keys."
msgstr ""
"uporabnik je ključ onemogočil (označil za neuporabo). Prezrt za &smime; "
"ključe."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2804
#, no-c-format
msgid "is-root-certificate"
msgstr "je-korensko-potrdilo"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2806
#, no-c-format
msgid "the key is a root certificate. Ignored for &openpgp; keys."
msgstr "ključ je korensko potrdilo. Prezrto za &openpgp; ključe."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2812
#, no-c-format
msgid "can-encrypt"
msgstr "lahko-šifrira"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2814
#, no-c-format
msgid "the key can be used for encryption."
msgstr "ključ se lahko uporablja za šifriranje."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2819
#, no-c-format
msgid "can-sign"
msgstr "lahko-podpiše"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2821
#, no-c-format
msgid "the key can be used for signing."
msgstr "ključ se lahko uporablja za podpis."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2826
#, no-c-format
msgid "can-certify"
msgstr "lahko-potrdi"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2828
#, no-c-format
msgid "the key can be used for signing (certifying) other keys."
msgstr "ključ se lahko uporablja za podpisovanje (potrjevanje) drugih ključev."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2834
#, no-c-format
msgid "can-authenticate"
msgstr "lahko-avtentificira"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2836
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"the key can be used for authentication (&eg; as an <acronym>TLS</acronym> "
"client certificate)."
msgstr ""
"ključ se lahko uporablja za avtentikacijo (npr. kot potrdilo odjemalca "
"<acronym>TLS</acronym>)."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2842
#, no-c-format
msgid "is-qualified"
msgstr "je-kvalificiran"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2844
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"the key can be used to make Qualified Signatures (as defined by the German "
"Digital Signature Law)."
msgstr ""
"ključ se lahko uporablja za izdelavo kvalificiranih podpisov (kot določa "
"nemški zakon o digitalnem podpisu)."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2850
#, no-c-format
msgid "is-cardkey"
msgstr "je-kartični-ključ"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2852
#, no-c-format
msgid "the key material is stored on a smartcard (instead of on the computer)."
msgstr ""
"ključno gradivo je shranjeno na pametni kartici (namesto na računalniku)."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2858
#, no-c-format
msgid "has-secret-key"
msgstr "ima-skrivni-ključ"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2860
#, no-c-format
msgid "the secret key for this key pair is available."
msgstr "skrivni ključ za ta par ključev je na voljo."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2865
#, no-c-format
msgid "is-openpgp-key"
msgstr "je-openpgp-ključ"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2867
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"the key is an &openpgp; key (<literal>true</literal>), or an &smime; key "
"(<literal>false</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"ključ je &openpgp; ključ (<literal>true</literal>) ali &smime; ključ "
"(<literal>false</literal>)."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2873
#, no-c-format
msgid "was-validated"
msgstr "bil-potrjeno"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2875
#, no-c-format
msgid "the key has been validated."
msgstr "ključ je bil preverjen."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2880
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>prefix</replaceable>-ownertrust"
msgstr "<replaceable>predpona</replaceable>-ownertrust"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2881 index.docbook:2914
#, no-c-format
msgid "validity"
msgstr "veljavnost"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2883
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Validity is an (ordered) enumeration with the following allowed values: "
"<literal>unknown</literal>, <literal>undefined</literal>, <literal>never</"
"literal>, <literal>marginal</literal>, <literal>full</literal>, "
"<literal>ultimate</literal>. See the &gpg; and &gpgsm; manuals for a "
"detailed explanation."
msgstr ""
"Veljavnost je (urejeno) oštevilčenje z naslednjimi dovoljenimi vrednostmi: "
"<literal>neznano</literal>, <literal>nedefinirano</literal>, "
"<literal>nikoli</literal>, <literal>obrobno</literal>, <literal>poln</"
"literal>, <literal>končni</literal>. Oglejte si &gpg; in &gpgsm; priročnike "
"za podrobno razlago."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2895
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"the key has exactly (<replaceable>prefix</replaceable>&nbsp;=&nbsp;"
"<literal>is</literal>), has anything but (<replaceable>prefix</"
"replaceable>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<literal>is-not</literal>), has at least "
"(<replaceable>prefix</replaceable>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<literal>is-at-least</"
"literal>), or has at most (<replaceable>prefix</replaceable>&nbsp;=&nbsp;"
"<literal>is-at-most</literal>) the ownertrust given as the value of the "
"config key. If more than one <varname><replaceable>prefix</replaceable>-"
"ownertrust</varname> keys (with different <replaceable>prefix</replaceable> "
"values) are present in a single group, the behavior is undefined."
msgstr ""
"ključ ima natanko (<replaceable>predpona</replaceable>&nbsp;=&nbsp;"
"<literal>je</literal>), ima karkoli drugega kot (<replaceable>prefix</"
"replaceable>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<literal>ni</literal>), ima najmanj "
"(<replaceable>predpona</replaceable>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<literal>je-končno</"
"literal>) ali ima največ (<replaceable>predpona</replaceable>&nbsp;=&nbsp;"
"<literal>je-največ</literal>) lastniško zaupanje, podano kot vrednost "
"konfiguracijskega ključa. Če je v eni skupini več kot en ključ "
"<varname><replaceable>predpona</replaceable>-ownertrust</varname> (z "
"različnimi vrednostmi <replaceable>predpona</replaceable>), je vedenje "
"nedefinirano."

#. Tag: varname
#: index.docbook:2913
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>prefix</replaceable>-validity"
msgstr "<replaceable>predpona</replaceable>-veljavnost"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:2915
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Analogous to <varname><replaceable>prefix</replaceable>-ownertrust</"
"varname>, but for key validity instead of ownertrust."
msgstr ""
"Enako kot <varname><replaceable>predpona</replaceable>-ownertrust</varname>, "
"vendar za veljavnost ključa namesto lastniškega zaupanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2926
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some of the more interesting criteria, such as <varname>is-revoked</varname> "
"or <varname>is-expired</varname> will only work on <emphasis>validated</"
"emphasis> keys, which is why, by default, only validated keys are checked "
"for revocation and expiration, although you are free to remove these extra "
"checks."
msgstr ""
"Nekateri bolj zanimivi kriteriji, kot je <varname>je-preklican</varname> ali "
"<varname>je-potekel</varname>, bodo delovali samo na <emphasis>preverjenih</"
"emphasis> ključih, zato se privzeto, samo potrjeni ključi preverijo glede "
"preklica in poteka, čeprav lahko ta dodatna preverjanja prosto odstranite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2937
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition to the config keys listed above, a key filter may also have an "
"<varname>id</varname> and <varname>match-contexts</varname>."
msgstr ""
"Poleg zgoraj navedenih konfiguracijskih ključev ima lahko filter ključev "
"tudi <varname>id</varname> in <varname>konteksti-ujemanja</varname>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2943
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the filter's <varname>id</varname>, which defaults to the filter's "
"config group name if not given or empty, you can reference the key filter "
"elsewhere in the configuration, &eg; in &kleopatra;'s View configurations. "
"The <varname>id</varname> is not interpreted by &kleopatra;, so you can use "
"any string you like, as long as it's unique."
msgstr ""
"Z uporabo <varname>id</varname> filtra, ki je privzeto ime konfiguracijske "
"skupine filtra, če ni podano ali je prazno, se lahko sklicujete na ključni "
"filter drugje v konfiguraciji, npr. v kleopatrinih konfiguracijah pogleda. "
"&kleopatra; ne interpretira <varname>id</varname>ja, zato lahko uporabite "
"poljuben niz, če je unikaten."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2953
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <varname>match-contexts</varname> limits the applicability of the "
"filter. Two contexts are currently defined: The <literal>appearance</"
"literal> context is used when defining coloring and font properties for the "
"views. The <literal>filtering</literal> context is used to selectively "
"include (and exclude) certificate from views. <literal>any</literal> can be "
"used to signify all currently defined contexts, and is the default if "
"<varname>match-contexts</varname> is not given, or otherwise produces no "
"contexts. This ensures that no key filter can end up <quote>dead</quote>, "
"&ie; with no contexts to apply it in."
msgstr ""
"<varname>konteksti-ujemanja</varname> omejuje uporabnost filtra. Trenutno "
"sta definirana dva konteksta: Kontekst <literal>videz</literal> se uporablja "
"pri definiranju barv in lastnosti pisave za poglede. Kontekst "
"<literal>filtriranja</literal> se uporablja za selektivno vključitev (in "
"izključitev) potrdila iz pogledov. <literal>vsak</literal> se lahko "
"uporablja za označevanje vseh trenutno definiranih kontekstov in je privzeta "
"vrednost, če <varname>konteksti-ujemanja</varname> ni podan ali kako drugače "
"ne proizvaja kontekstov. To zagotavlja, da noben ključni filter ne more "
"<quote>mrtev</quote>, tj. brez kontekstov, v katerih bi ga uporabili."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2967
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The format of the entry is a list of tokens, separated by non-word "
"characters. Each of the tokens is optionally prefixed by an exclamation "
"point (<literal>!</literal>), indicating negation. The tokens act in order "
"on an internal list of contexts, which starts out empty. This is best "
"explained by an example: <literal>any !appearance</literal> is the same as "
"<literal>filtering</literal>, and <literal>appearance !appearance</literal> "
"is producing the empty set, as is <literal>!any</literal>. However, the last "
"two will be internally replaced by <literal>any</literal>, since they "
"produce no contexts at all."
msgstr ""
"Format vnosa je seznam žetonov, ločenih z nebesednimi znaki. Pred vsakim "
"žetonom je izbirno predpona s klicajem (<literal>!</literal>), ki označuje "
"zanikanje. Žetoni delujejo po vrstnem redu na notranjem seznamu kontekstov, "
"ki se začne prazen. To je najbolje razloženo s primerom: <literal>kateri "
"koli !appearance</literal> je enak kot <literal>filtriranje</literal> in "
"<literal>videz !appearance</literal> proizvaja prazen niz, kot je <literal>!"
"any</literal>. Vendar bosta zadnja dva interno nadomeščena z <literal>any</"
"literal>, ker sploh ne proizvajata kontekstov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2981
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In general, criteria not specified (&ie; the config entry is not set) are "
"not checked for. If a criterion is given, it is checked for and must match "
"for the filter as a whole to match, &ie; the criteria are AND'ed together."
msgstr ""
"Na splošno se kriteriji, ki niso podani (tj. vnos konfiguracije ni "
"nastavljen), ne preverjajo. Če je podan kriterij, se preveri, ali se mora "
"ujemati, da se filter kot celota ujema, tj. kriteriji so združeni z IN."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2988
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each filter has an implied <quote>specificity</quote> that is used to rank "
"all matching filters. The more specific filter wins over less specific ones. "
"If two filters have the same specificity, the one that comes first in the "
"config file wins. A filter's specificity is proportional to the number of "
"criteria it contains."
msgstr ""
"Vsak filter ima implicirano <quote>specifičnost</quote>, ki se uporablja za "
"razvrščanje vseh ujemajočih se filtrov. Bolj specifični filter zmaga pred "
"manj specifičnimi. Če imata dva filtra enako specifičnost, zmaga tisti, ki "
"je prvi v konfiguracijski datoteki. Specifičnost filtra je sorazmerna s "
"številom kriterijev, ki jih vsebuje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2998
#, no-c-format
msgid "Examples of key filters"
msgstr "Primeri ključnih filtrov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2999
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To check for all expired, but non-revoked root certificates, you would use a "
"key filter defined as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Če želite preveriti vsa potekla, vendar nepreklicana korenska potrdila, bi "
"uporabili filter ključev, definiran na naslednji način:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:3004
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<!--\n"
"-->[Key Filter #<replaceable>n</replaceable>]\n"
"Name=expired, but not revoked\n"
"was-validated=true\n"
"is-expired=true\n"
"is-revoked=false\n"
"is-root-certificate=true\n"
"; ( specificity 4 )<!--\n"
"     -->"
msgstr ""
"<!--\n"
"-->[Filter ključev #<replaceable>n</replaceable>]\n"
"Name=potekel, ampak ni preklican\n"
"je-bil-potrjen=true\n"
"je-potekel=true\n"
"je-preklican=false\n"
"je-korenski-certifikat=true\n"
"; ( specificity 4 )<!--\n"
"     -->"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3005
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To check for all disabled &openpgp; keys (not yet supported by &kleopatra;) "
"with ownertrust of at least <quote>marginal</quote>, you would use:"
msgstr ""
"Za preverjanje vseh onemogočenih &openpgp; ključev (ki jih kleopatra še ne "
"podpira) z lastniškim zaupanjem vsaj <quote>mejno</quote>, bi uporabili:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:3010
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<!--\n"
"-->[Key Filter #<replaceable>n</replaceable>]\n"
"Name=disabled OpenPGP keys with marginal or better ownertrust\n"
"is-openpgp=true\n"
"is-disabled=true\n"
"is-at-least-ownertrust=marginal\n"
"; ( specificity 3 )<!--\n"
"     -->"
msgstr ""
"<!--\n"
"-->[Key Filter #<replaceable>n</replaceable>]\n"
"Ime=onemogočeni ključi OpenPGP z obrobnim ali boljšim lastniškim zaupanjem\n"
"je-openpgp=true\n"
"je-onemogočen=true\n"
"je-vsaj-lastniško-zaupanje=mejno\n"
"; ( specificity 3 )<!--\n"
"     -->"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:3017
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Archivers for Use with Sign/Encrypt Files"
msgstr ""
"Konfiguriranje arhivarjev za uporabo s podpisovanjem/šifriranjem datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3019
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; allows the administrator (and power-user) to configure the list "
"of archivers that are presented in the Sign/Encrypt Files dialog."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; omogoča skrbniku (in naprednemu uporabniku), da konfigurira "
"seznam arhivarjev, ki so predstavljeni v pogovornem oknu podpiši/šifriraj "
"datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3025
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each archiver is defined in <filename>libkleopatrarc</filename> as a "
"separate <literal>Archive&nbsp;Definition&nbsp;#<replaceable>n</"
"replaceable></literal> group, with the following mandatory keys:"
msgstr ""
"Vsak arhivar je definiran v <filename>libkleopatrarc</filename> kot ločena "
"skupina <literal>Arhiviraj&nbsp;Definicija&nbsp;#<replaceable>n</"
"replaceable></literal> z naslednjimi obveznimi ključi:"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:3035
#, no-c-format
msgid "extensions"
msgstr "razširitve"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3037
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A comma-separated list of filename extensions that usually indicate this "
"archive format."
msgstr ""
"Seznam končnic imen datotek, ločenih z vejicami, ki običajno označujejo to "
"obliko arhiva."

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:3045 index.docbook:3288
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>id</literal>"
msgstr "<literal>id</literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3047
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A unique ID used to identify this archiver internally. If in doubt, use the "
"name of the command."
msgstr ""
"Enolični ID, ki se uporablja za notranjo identifikacijo tega arhivarja. Če "
"ste v dvomih, uporabite ime ukaza."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:3055 index.docbook:3298
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>Name</literal> (translated)"
msgstr "<literal>Ime</literal> (prevedeno)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3057
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The user-visible name of this archiver, as shown in the corresponding drop-"
"down menu of the Sign/Encrypt Files dialog."
msgstr ""
"Uporabniku vidno ime tega arhivarja, kot je prikazano v ustreznem spustnem "
"meniju pogovornega okna podpiši/šifriraj datoteke."

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:3066
#, no-c-format
msgid "pack-command"
msgstr "pack-ukaz"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3068
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The actual command to archive files. You can use any command, as long as no "
"shell is required to execute it. The program file is looked up using the "
"<envar>PATH</envar> environment variable, unless you use an absolute file "
"path. Quoting is supported as if a shell was used:"
msgstr ""
"Dejanski ukaz za arhiviranje datotek. Uporabite lahko kateri koli ukaz, če "
"za njegovo izvedbo ni potrebna lupina. Programsko datoteko poiščete s "
"spremenljivko okolja <envar>PATH</envar>, razen če uporabite absolutno pot "
"do datoteke. Citiranje je podprto, kot če bi bila uporabljena lupina:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:3075
#, no-c-format
msgid "pack-command=\"/opt/ZIP v2.32/bin/zip\" -r -"
msgstr "pack-command=\"/opt/ZIP v2.32/bin/zip\" -r -"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3083
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since backslash (<literal>\\</literal>) is an escape character in &kde; "
"config files, you need to double them when they appear in path names: "
"<programlisting>pack-command=C:\\\\Programs\\\\GNU\\\\tar\\\\gtar."
"exe&nbsp;...</programlisting> However, for the command itself (as opposed to "
"its arguments), you may just use forward slashes (<literal>/</literal>) as "
"path separators on all platforms: <programlisting>pack-command=C:/Programs/"
"GNU/tar/gtar.exe&nbsp;...</programlisting> This is not supported in "
"arguments, as most &Windows; programs use the forward slash for options. For "
"example, the following will not work, since <literal>C:/myarchivescript.bat</"
"literal> is an argument to <command>cmd.exe</command>, and <literal>/</"
"literal> is not converted to <literal>\\</literal> in arguments, only "
"commands: <programlisting>pack-command=cmd.exe C:/myarchivescript.bat</"
"programlisting> This needs, instead, to be written as:"
msgstr ""
"Ker je poševnica nazaj (<literal>\\</literal>) ubežni znak v &kde; "
"konfiguracijskih datotek, jih morate podvojiti, ko se pojavijo v imenih "
"poti: <programlisting>pack-command=C:\\\\Programs\\\\GNU\\\\tar\\\\gtar."
"exe&nbsp;...</programlisting> Vendar za sam ukaz (v nasprotju z njegovimi "
"argumenti), lahko uporabite samo poševnice (<literal>/</literal>) kot ločila "
"poti na vseh platformah: <programlisting>pack-command=C:/Programs/GNU/tar/"
"gtar.exe&nbsp;...</programlisting> To ni podprto v argumentih, saj večina "
"&Windows; programov uporabljajo poševnico naprej za možnosti. Naslednje na "
"primer ne bo delovalo, ker je <literal>C:/myarchivescript.bat</literal> "
"argument za <command>cmd.exe</command> in <literal>/</literal> ni pretvorjen "
"v <literal>\\</literal> v argumentih samo ukazi: <programlisting>pack-"
"command=cmd.exe C:/myarchivescript.bat</programlisting> To mora biti namesto "
"tega zapisano kot:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:3104
#, no-c-format
msgid "pack-command=cmd.exe C:\\\\myarchivescript.bat"
msgstr "pack-command=cmd.exe C:\\\\myarchivescript.bat"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:3110
#, no-c-format
msgid "Input Filename Passing for <literal>pack-command</literal>"
msgstr "Vhodno ime datoteke Posredovanje za <literal>pack-command</literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are three ways to pass filenames to the pack command. For each of "
"these, <literal>pack-command</literal> provides a particular syntax:"
msgstr ""
"Obstajajo trije načini za posredovanje imen datotek ukazu pack. Za vsakega "
"od teh <literal>pack-command</literal>ov zagotavlja posebno sintakso:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3121
#, no-c-format
msgid "As command-line arguments."
msgstr "Kot argumente ukazne vrstice."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Example (tar): <programlisting>pack-command=tar cf -</programlisting> "
"Example (zip): <programlisting>pack-command=zip -r - %f</programlisting> In "
"this case, filenames are passed on the command line, just like you would "
"when using the command prompt. &kleopatra; does not use a shell to execute "
"the command. Therefore, this is a safe way of passing filenames, but it "
"might run into command line length restrictions on some platforms. A literal "
"<literal>%f</literal>, if present, is replaced by the names of the files to "
"archive. Otherwise, filenames are appended to the command line. Thus, the "
"zip Example above could equivalently be written like this:"
msgstr ""
"Primer (tar): <programlisting>pack-command=tar cf -</programlisting> Primer "
"(zip): <programlisting>pack-command=zip -r - %f</programlisting> V tem "
"primeru se imena datotek posredujejo na ukazno vrstico, tako kot pri uporabi "
"ukazne vrstice. &kleopatra; ne uporablja ukazne lupine za izvedbo ukaza. "
"Zato je to varen način posredovanja imen datotek, vendar lahko na nekaterih "
"platformah naleti na omejitve dolžine ukazne vrstice. Dobesedni <literal>%f</"
"literal>, če je prisoten, se nadomesti z imeni datotek za arhiviranje. V "
"nasprotnem primeru so imena datotek dodana ukazni vrstici. Tako bi lahko "
"zgornji primer zip enakovredno zapisal takole:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:3138
#, no-c-format
msgid "pack-command=zip -r -"
msgstr "pack-command=zip -r -"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3143
#, no-c-format
msgid "Via standard-in, separated by newlines: prepend <literal>|</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Prek standardnega vstopa, ločeno z novimi vrsticami: pred <literal>|</"
"literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Example (&GNU;-tar): <programlisting>pack-command=|gtar cf - -T-</"
"programlisting> Example (ZIP): <programlisting>pack-command=|zip -@ -</"
"programlisting> In this case, filenames are passed to the archiver on "
"<acronym>stdin</acronym>, one per line. This avoids problems on platforms "
"which place a low limit on the number of command line arguments that are "
"allowed, but fails when filenames, in fact, contain newlines."
msgstr ""
"Primer (&GNU;-tar): <programlisting>pack-command=|gtar cf - -T-</"
"programlisting> Primer (ZIP): <programlisting>pack-command=|zip -@ -</"
"programlisting> V tem primeru , so imena datotek posredovana arhivatorju na "
"<acronym>stdin</acronym>, eno na vrstico. S tem se izognete težavam na "
"platformah, ki postavljajo nizko omejitev števila dovoljenih argumentov "
"ukazne vrstice, vendar ne uspe, če imena datotek dejansko vsebujejo nove "
"vrstice."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; currently only supports <acronym>LF</acronym> as a newline "
"separator, not <acronym>CRLF</acronym>. This might change in future "
"versions, based on user feedback."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; trenutno podpira samo <acronym>LF</acronym> kot ločilo za novo "
"vrstico, ne pa <acronym>CRLF</acronym>. To se lahko spremeni v prihodnjih "
"različicah na podlagi povratnih informacij uporabnikov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3167
#, no-c-format
msgid "Via standard-in, separated by NUL-bytes: prepend <literal>0|</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Preko standardnega vhoda, ločenega z NUL-bajti: pred <literal>0|</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3168
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Example (&GNU;-tar): <programlisting>pack-command=0|gtar cf - -T- --null</"
"programlisting> This is the same as above, except that NUL bytes are used to "
"separate filenames. Since NUL bytes are forbidden in filenames, this is the "
"most robust way of passing filenames, but not all archivers support it."
msgstr ""
"Primer (&GNU;-tar): <programlisting>pack-command=0|gtar cf - -T- --null</"
"programlisting> To je enako kot zgoraj, le da se za ločevanje imen datotek "
"uporabljajo NUL bajti. Ker so NUL bajti v imenih datotek prepovedani, je to "
"najbolj robusten način posredovanja imen datotek, vendar ga ne podpirajo vsi "
"arhivi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:3186
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Checksum Programs for Use with Create/Verify Checksums"
msgstr ""
"Konfiguriranje programov za kontrolne vsote za uporabo z ustvarjanjem/"
"preverjanjem kontrolnih vsot"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kleopatra; allows the administrator (and power-user) to configure the list "
"of checksum programs that the user can choose from in the config dialog and "
"that &kleopatra; is able to auto-detect when asked to verify a given file's "
"checksum."
msgstr ""
"&kleopatra; omogoča skrbniku (in izkušenemu uporabniku), da konfigurira "
"seznam programov za preverjanje vsote, med katerimi lahko uporabnik izbira v "
"konfiguracijskem pogovornem oknu in da &kleopatra; lahko samodejno zazna, ko "
"se zahteva, da preveri kontrolno vsoto dane datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3196
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To be usable by &kleopatra;, output of checksum programs (both the written "
"checksum file, as well as the output on <acronym>stdout</acronym> when "
"verifying checksums) needs to be compatible with &GNU; <command>md5sum</"
"command> and <command>sha1sum</command>."
msgstr ""
"Da bi ga lahko uporabljal program &kleopatra;, mora biti izhod programov za "
"kontrolne vsote (tako zapisana datoteka s kontrolno vsoto kot tudi izhod na "
"<acronym>stdout</acronym> pri preverjanju kontrolnih vsot) združljiv z &GNU; "
"<command>md5sum</command> in <command>sha1sum</command>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifically, the checksum file needs to be line-based with each line having "
"the following format: <programlisting><replaceable>CHECKSUM</replaceable> ' "
"' ( ' ' | '*' ) <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable></programlisting> where "
"<replaceable>CHECKSUM</replaceable> consists of hex-characters only. If "
"<replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable> contains a newline character, the line "
"must instead read: <programlisting>\\<replaceable>CHECKSUM</replaceable> ' "
"' ( ' ' | '*' ) <replaceable>ESCAPED-FILENAME</replaceable></programlisting> "
"where <replaceable>ESCAPED-FILENAME</replaceable> is the filename with "
"newlines replaced by <literal>\\n</literal>s, and backslashes doubled "
"(<literal>\\</literal>&#x21A6;<literal>\\\\</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"Natančneje, datoteka s kontrolno vsoto mora temeljiti na vrstici, pri čemer "
"ima vsaka vrstica naslednjo obliko: <programlisting><replaceable>CHECKSUM</"
"replaceable> ' ' ( ' ' | '*' ) <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable></"
"programlisting>, kjer je <replaceable>CHECKSUM</replaceable> sestavljen samo "
"iz šestnajstiških znakov. Če <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable> vsebuje "
"znak za novo vrstico, se mora vrstica namesto tega glasiti: <programlisting>"
"\\<replaceable>CHECKSUM</replaceable> ' ' ( ' ' | '*' ) <replaceable>ESCAPED-"
"FILENAME</replaceable></programlisting>, kjer je <replaceable>ESCAPED-"
"FILENAME</replaceable> ime datoteke z novimi vrsticami, zamenjanimi z "
"<literal>\\n</literal>ji, in poševnicami nazaj (<literal>\\</literal>&#x21A6;"
"<literal>\\\\</literal>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3223
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Similarly, the output of <xref linkend=\"checksum-definition-verify-command"
"\"/> must be of the form <programlisting><replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable> "
"( ': OK' | ': FAILED' )</programlisting> separated by newlines. Newlines and "
"other characters are <emphasis>not</emphasis> escaped in the output."
msgstr ""
"Podobno mora biti izhod <xref linkend=\"checksum-definition-verify-command\"/"
"> v obliki <programlisting><replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable> ( ': OK' | ': "
"FAILED' )</programlisting > ločeno z novo vrstico. Nove vrstice in drugi "
"znaki <emphasis>niso</emphasis> ubežni v izpisu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Yes, these programs were not written with graphical frontends in mind, and "
"&kleopatra; will fail to correctly parse pathological filenames that contain "
"\":&nbsp;OK\" plus newline in them."
msgstr ""
"Da, ti programi niso bili napisani z mislijo na grafične vmesnike in program "
"&kleopatra; ne bo uspel pravilno razčleniti patoloških imen datotek, ki "
"vsebujejo »:&nbsp;OK« in novo vrstico."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each checksum program is defined in <filename>libkleopatrarc</filename> as a "
"separate <literal>Checksum&nbsp;Definition&nbsp;#<replaceable>n</"
"replaceable></literal> group, with the following mandatory keys:"
msgstr ""
"Vsak program kontrolne vsote je definiran v <filename>libkleopatrarc</"
"filename> kot ločena skupina <literal>Checksum&nbsp;Definition&nbsp;"
"#<replaceable>n</replaceable></literal> z naslednjimi obveznimi ključi:"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:3252
#, no-c-format
msgid "file-patterns"
msgstr "vzorci-datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A list of regular expressions that describe which files should be considered "
"checksum files for this checksum program. The syntax is the one used for "
"string lists in &kde; config files. <note> <para> Since regular expressions "
"usually contain backslashes, care must be taken to properly escape them in "
"the config file. The use of a config file editing tool is recommended. </"
"para> </note> The platform defines whether the patterns are treated case-"
"sensitive or case-insensitive."
msgstr ""
"Seznam regularnih izrazov, ki opisujejo, katere datoteke je treba "
"obravnavati kot datoteke kontrolne vsote za ta program kontrolne vsote. "
"Sintaksa je tista, ki se uporablja za sezname nizov v &kde; konfiguracijskih "
"datotekah. <note> <para> Ker regularni izrazi običajno vsebujejo poševnice "
"nazaj, je treba v konfiguracijski datoteki paziti, da jim pravilno ubežite. "
"Priporočljiva je uporaba orodja za urejanje konfiguracijske datoteke. </"
"para> </note> Platforma določa, ali se vzorci obravnavajo med velikimi ali "
"malimi črkami."

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:3274
#, no-c-format
msgid "output-file"
msgstr "izhodna-datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3276
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The typical output filename for this checksum program (should match one of "
"the <xref linkend=\"checksum-definition-file-patterns\"/>, of course). This "
"is what &kleopatra; will use as the output filename when creating checksum "
"files of this type."
msgstr ""
"Tipično ime izhodne datoteke za ta program za preverjanje vsote (seveda se "
"mora ujemati z enim od <xref linkend=\"checksum-definition-file-patterns\"/"
">). To je tisto, kar bo program &kleopatra; uporabil kot izhodno ime "
"datoteke pri ustvarjanju datotek s kontrolno vsoto te vrste."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A unique ID used to identify this checksum program internally. If in doubt, "
"use the name of the command."
msgstr ""
"Enolični ID, ki se uporablja za interno identifikacijo tega programa "
"kontrolne vsote. Če ste v dvomih, uporabite ime ukaza."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3300
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The user-visible name of this checksum program, as shown in the drop-down "
"menu in &kleopatra;'s config dialog."
msgstr ""
"Uporabniku vidno ime tega programa kontrolne vsote, kot je prikazano v "
"spustnem meniju v konfiguracijskem pogovornem oknu programa &kleopatra;."

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:3308
#, no-c-format
msgid "create-command"
msgstr "ustvari-ukaz"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3310
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The actual command with which to create checksum files. The syntax, "
"restrictions and argument passing options are the same as described for "
"<xref linkend=\"archive-definition-pack-command\"/> in <xref linkend=\"admin-"
"archive-definitions\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Dejanski ukaz, s katerim ustvarite datoteke s kontrolno vsoto. Sintaksa, "
"omejitve in možnosti posredovanja argumentov so enake, kot je opisano za "
"<xref linkend=\"archive-definition-pack-command\"/> v <xref linkend=\"admin-"
"archive-definitions\"/>."

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:3321
#, no-c-format
msgid "verify-command"
msgstr "ukaz-za-preverjanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Same as <xref linkend=\"checksum-definition-create-command\"/>, but for "
"checksum verification."
msgstr ""
"Enako kot <xref linkend=\"checksum-definition-create-command\"/>, vendar za "
"preverjanje kontrolne vsote."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3333
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is a complete example:"
msgstr "Tu je popoln primer:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:3335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"[Checksum Definition #1]\n"
"          file-patterns=sha1sum.txt\n"
"          output-file=sha1sum.txt\n"
"          id=sha1sum-gnu\n"
"          Name=sha1sum (GNU)\n"
"          Name[de]=sha1sum (GNU)\n"
"          ...\n"
"          create-command=sha1sum -- %f\n"
"          verify-command=sha1sum -c -- %f"
msgstr ""
"[Checksum Definition #1]\n"
"          file-patterns=sha1sum.txt\n"
"          output-file=sha1sum.txt\n"
"          id=sha1sum-gnu\n"
"          Name=sha1sum (GNU)\n"
"          Name[de]=sha1sum (GNU)\n"
"          ...\n"
"          create-command=sha1sum -- %f\n"
"          verify-command=sha1sum -c -- %f"

